1
00:00:11,612 --> 00:00:13,814
NAME'S JORDY--

2
00:00:13,814 --> 00:00:16,250
JORDY REMBRANDT.

3
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:20,153
I GREW UP ON THE
SOUTH SIDE OF THE CITY.

4
00:00:21,121 --> 00:00:23,156
THIS IS MY HIGH SCHOOL.

5
00:00:24,458 --> 00:00:26,760
OR SHOULD I SAY "WAS"...

6
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:29,529
LIKE MOST PUBLIC SCHOOLS
IN ANY CITY

7
00:00:29,529 --> 00:00:31,665
THE CLASSES WERE TOUGH...

8
00:00:31,665 --> 00:00:33,901
[slam... thump]

9
00:00:35,903 --> 00:00:37,938
MORNIN'!

10
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:40,340
ADMISSION WAS
HIGHLY COMPETITIVE.

11
00:00:40,340 --> 00:00:44,778
AND THERE SEEMED TO BE AN
OVER-EMPHASIS PLACED ON
ATHLETICS.

12
00:00:44,778 --> 00:00:46,713
SO WHEN MY COUNSELOR SUGGESTED

13
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:50,751
A CHANGE OF VENUE MIGHT IMPROVE
MY CHANCES OF GRADUATING...

14
00:00:50,751 --> 00:00:53,086
YOUR HONOR, WE DO THROW
 OURSELVES

15
00:00:53,086 --> 00:00:55,122
AT THE MERCY OF THIS
 COURT.

16
00:00:56,657 --> 00:00:58,926
BEARS SEASON TICKETS
 YOUR HONOR...

17
00:00:58,926 --> 00:01:00,427
YOU AND THE MISSUS.

18
00:01:00,427 --> 00:01:01,995
IT SOUNDED LIKE
WITH GOOD BEHAVIOR

19
00:01:01,995 --> 00:01:04,665
I COULD STILL GRADUATE
IN JUNE.

20
00:01:04,665 --> 00:01:07,000
TOUGH BREAK
 KID.

21
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,268
AH!... OOF!

22
00:01:08,268 --> 00:01:11,038
THIS IS MY NEW SCHOOL.

23
00:01:11,038 --> 00:01:13,173
OINK, OINK... MOO

24
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:15,676
LIKE MOST PUBLIC SCHOOLS
IN THE COUNTRY,

25
00:01:15,676 --> 00:01:18,645
IT TOO, HAS PROBLEMS...

26
00:01:18,645 --> 00:01:21,581
TODAY IT JUST GOT ONE MORE.

27
00:01:23,216 --> 00:01:25,018
ME.

28
00:01:25,018 --> 00:01:33,927
♪ [bright orchestral] ♪

29
00:01:36,496 --> 00:01:38,665
THEY'RE GONNA PAY.

30
00:01:38,665 --> 00:01:40,600
EASY, ICE.
   LAST YEAR

31
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,469
IT WAS A GIANT PINK
   JOCK STRAP!

32
00:01:42,469 --> 00:01:44,671
AND THEY SHAVED
   THE FRESHMEN CLASS.

33
00:01:44,671 --> 00:01:47,741
WHAT HAPPENED TO SECURITY
THIS YEAR FRESHMEN?

34
00:01:49,810 --> 00:01:52,212
THEY CAN'T DO THAT
TO OUR FRESHMEN.

35
00:01:52,212 --> 00:01:55,515
ONLY WE CAN DO THAT
TO OUR FRESHMEN.

36
00:01:55,515 --> 00:01:58,652
EVERYBODY HERE
   AGREE WITH ICE?  YEAH!

37
00:01:58,652 --> 00:02:00,587
EVERYBODY HERE THINK WE SHOULD
JUST MARCH OVER THERE

38
00:02:00,587 --> 00:02:02,689
AND BASH IN THE WINDSHIELDS
OF THEIR BMWs?

39
00:02:02,689 --> 00:02:04,691
YEAH, YEAH, GREAT!

40
00:02:04,691 --> 00:02:07,194
A MASCOT WITH
GENDER PROBLEMS.

41
00:02:07,194 --> 00:02:09,663
WHAT DID
   YOU SAY?

42
00:02:09,663 --> 00:02:11,298
I WAS TALKING
ABOUT YOGI.

43
00:02:11,298 --> 00:02:13,834
HE SEEMS TO BE HAVING
A BAD FUR DAY.

44
00:02:13,834 --> 00:02:15,402
DUDE, DON'T
   'DISS THE GRIZZ'.

45
00:02:15,402 --> 00:02:17,204
THAT'S A BIG DEAL
  AROUND HERE.

46
00:02:17,204 --> 00:02:19,973
BUT YOU'RE OBVIOUSLY
 NOT FROM AROUND HERE.

47
00:02:21,241 --> 00:02:22,876
CAREFUL THERE, COWBOY.

48
00:02:22,876 --> 00:02:24,378
HEY! KNOCK IT OFF YOU
   GUYS!

49
00:02:24,378 --> 00:02:25,946
THERE ARE BETTER WAYS
TO GET REVENGE.

50
00:02:25,946 --> 00:02:27,414
LIKE WHAT,
 MR. PRESIDENT?

51
00:02:27,414 --> 00:02:28,915
MAKE PEACE.

52
00:02:28,915 --> 00:02:30,550
OUR FIGHT IS NOT
WITH EACH OTHER,

53
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:32,352
THIS IS A FIGHT
TO DO WHAT'S RIGHT.

54
00:02:32,352 --> 00:02:34,154
I AGREE WITH CROWDER!.

55
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,889
AND THE RIGHT
   THING TO DO

56
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:37,824
IS TO STOMP THEIR
   BRAINS OUT.

57
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:39,459
(yelling)
   YEAH...YEAH!

58
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:41,495
HEY! YOU THINK THIS
   IS A BIG JOKE?

59
00:02:41,495 --> 00:02:42,996
YOU'RE THE ONE
DEFENDING THE CARE BEAR.

60
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,464
THAT KINDA MAKES YOU
THE BIG JOKE.

61
00:02:44,464 --> 00:02:46,400
YOU'RE A REAL FUNNY GUY.

62
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:49,036
I'D KINDA LIKE TO SPREAD
   SOME OF THAT HUMOR AROUND--

63
00:02:49,036 --> 00:02:50,604
THE SIDEWALK!

64
00:02:52,639 --> 00:02:55,275
THIS DUDE NEEDS
   TO LEARN SOME RESPECT.

65
00:02:55,275 --> 00:02:56,543
HE SURE DOES!

66
00:02:58,078 --> 00:03:00,313
ALL RIGHT COME ON-- 
   APOLOGIZE TO THE BEAR!

67
00:03:00,313 --> 00:03:01,815
[boys yelling]

68
00:03:01,815 --> 00:03:03,850
PROBLEM BOYS?

69
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:07,721
LAST DAY FOR SENIOR CLASS FLOAT
ENTRIES IS THIS FRIDAY.

70
00:03:07,721 --> 00:03:10,857
STUDENT COUNCIL WOULD ALSO LIKE
TO REMIND ALL STUDENTS

71
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:15,362
THAT A RESPONSE TO THE VANDALISM
DONE TO OUR SCHOOL

72
00:03:15,362 --> 00:03:18,265
WILL BE HANDLED
THROUGH THE COUNCIL.

73
00:03:18,265 --> 00:03:20,767
VANDALISM IS A CRIMINAL OFFENSE.

74
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:23,970
LET'S NOT SINK TO THEIR LEVEL
FOLKS. THANK YOU.

75
00:03:30,510 --> 00:03:32,512
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

76
00:03:32,512 --> 00:03:34,448
YOU SHOULD SEE THE OTHER GUY.

77
00:03:35,682 --> 00:03:38,785
I'LL BE LOOKING FOR YOU
AFTER SCHOOL.

78
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,722
HE LOOKS
  FINE TO ME.

79
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,658
MASSIVE INTERNAL INJURIES.

80
00:03:44,658 --> 00:03:46,326
IT'S UGLY.

81
00:03:46,326 --> 00:03:48,728
WELL... HOPE
YOU FEEL BETTER.

82
00:03:49,830 --> 00:03:51,198
YOU.

83
00:03:53,266 --> 00:03:56,870
JORDAN REMBRANDT.

84
00:03:56,870 --> 00:03:59,973
I'VE GOT YOUR FILE HERE -

85
00:03:59,973 --> 00:04:01,508
MOST OF IT ANYWAY -

86
00:04:01,508 --> 00:04:03,543
THE FAX MACHINE
IS STILL WORKING.

87
00:04:03,543 --> 00:04:06,379
YOU WERE SUSPENDED
   FOR FIGHTING.

88
00:04:06,379 --> 00:04:07,881
HE HIT ME FIRST.

89
00:04:07,881 --> 00:04:09,549
YOU WERE SUSPENDED 8
   TIMES.

90
00:04:09,549 --> 00:04:12,152
THEY ALL HIT ME FIRST.

91
00:04:12,152 --> 00:04:14,988
2-TIME ALL-STATE
   WIDE RECEIVER.

92
00:04:14,988 --> 00:04:18,391
THAT WAS UNTIL LAST MONTH
WHEN YOU PUNCHED YOUR COACH.

93
00:04:19,559 --> 00:04:21,962
YOU PUNCHED YOUR COACH?

94
00:04:21,962 --> 00:04:24,231
HE WAS GONNA HIT ME FIRST.

95
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,401
THE COURT SAYS WE'RE YOUR
LAST CHANCE

96
00:04:28,401 --> 00:04:29,603
YOU MESS UP AGAIN,

97
00:04:29,603 --> 00:04:31,905
AND IT'S BACK TO SUNNY RIDGE
BOYS HOME.

98
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:34,074
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE TO LEARN
HOW TO GET ALONG WITH OTHERS.

99
00:04:34,074 --> 00:04:36,009
I CAN DO THAT.

100
00:04:36,009 --> 00:04:38,178
I DON'T TOLERATE FIGHTING.

101
00:04:38,178 --> 00:04:40,580
ONE WEEK DETENTION STARTING
TODAY.

102
00:04:40,580 --> 00:04:44,317
AND I WANT YOU SIGNED UP FOR
2 AFTER SCHOOL ACTIVITIES

103
00:04:44,317 --> 00:04:46,787
STARTING MONDAY.

104
00:04:48,755 --> 00:04:50,991
BRING ME
   WRITTEN PROOF.

105
00:04:52,626 --> 00:04:57,264
WOULD DETENTION BE CONSIDERED
AN AFTER SCHOOL ACTIVITY?

106
00:04:57,264 --> 00:05:01,067
PHILANTHROPIC CLUBS,
   SPORTS ACTIVITIES

107
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:03,570
I WANT WRITTEN PROOF.

108
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:05,805
GO-- SEE THE NURSE.

109
00:05:07,274 --> 00:05:08,742
OH--

110
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,078
WELCOME TO MORRIS.

111
00:05:13,513 --> 00:05:15,315
GO GRIZZLIES.

112
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:19,085
THE AFRICAN TREE FROG

113
00:05:19,085 --> 00:05:21,254
IS ABLE TO ADAPT
TO ITS SURROUNDINGS.

114
00:05:21,254 --> 00:05:25,325
IT DOES THIS AS A NATURAL
DEFENSE AGAINST PREDATORS.

115
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:29,663
BY BLENDING WITH PLANT LIFE
IN THE BIOSPHERE -

116
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:32,732
A TECHNIQUE KNOWN AS
"CAMOUFLAGING" -

117
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:36,369
NATURE PROTECTS
THIS HARMLESS AMPHIBIAN

118
00:05:36,369 --> 00:05:39,606
FROM ITS HOSTILE ENVIRONMENT.

119
00:05:39,606 --> 00:05:41,775
LIGHTS PLEASE.

120
00:05:41,775 --> 00:05:43,343
(Wally)
ANYONE-- LIGHTS!

121
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:45,011
AHHHHHHHH...!

122
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:46,580
(screaming)
GET 'EM OFF ME.

123
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:48,215
THEY'RE SUCKING
OUT MY EYEBALLS!

124
00:05:48,215 --> 00:05:50,183
GET 'EM OFF ME!

125
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:52,419
AAAHHHHH!

126
00:05:52,419 --> 00:05:54,187
[students chattering]

127
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:56,356
QUITE HARMLESS, ACTUALLY.

128
00:05:57,424 --> 00:05:58,992
RIBIT!

129
00:05:58,992 --> 00:06:02,195
[students laughing]

130
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:17,077
♪ [medium-paced
flute & strings] ♪

131
00:06:17,077 --> 00:06:32,592
♪   ♪

132
00:06:32,592 --> 00:06:34,995
(The Dean)
  SIGN THE ROLL, TAKE A SEAT.

133
00:06:34,995 --> 00:06:36,663
THANKS--
BROUGHT MY OWN.

134
00:06:36,663 --> 00:06:38,398
NO TALKING.

135
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:57,751
♪    ♪

136
00:06:57,751 --> 00:07:00,387
[bell rings]

137
00:07:00,387 --> 00:07:02,022
NEED A RIDE HOME?

138
00:07:02,022 --> 00:07:05,492
UH, I CAN WALK.

139
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:09,262
I MEAN AH...

140
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:12,465
SURE... WHATEVER.

141
00:07:14,401 --> 00:07:15,969
I DON'T LIKE
SPECIAL TREATMENT.

142
00:07:15,969 --> 00:07:17,804
THAT'S WHY I PARK
OUT HERE IN THE LOT.

143
00:07:17,804 --> 00:07:20,273
BY THE WAY, I'M WALLY.

144
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:22,809
(Jordy) WHO'S THAT GIRL?
(Wally) THAT'S PAM...

145
00:07:22,809 --> 00:07:24,844
WE'RE SORT OF AN ITEM.

146
00:07:24,844 --> 00:07:27,147
BUT DON'T SAY ANYTHING.
IT'S A SURPRISE.

147
00:07:27,147 --> 00:07:28,948
TO WHO?
 PAM.

148
00:07:31,051 --> 00:07:32,552
HEY PAM.

149
00:07:32,552 --> 00:07:34,254
HEY!
THIS IS JORDY.

150
00:07:34,254 --> 00:07:37,023
YUP, I KNOW--
   JORDY REMBRANDT.

151
00:07:37,023 --> 00:07:40,460
I CHANGED THE PAPER IN THE FAX
MACHINE THIS MORNING SO...

152
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:42,696
SO YOU'VE SEEN ALL MY
  MERIT SCHOLARSHIP AWARDS.

153
00:07:42,696 --> 00:07:44,731
HEY PAM, COMIN' TO CLC
FRIDAY NIGHT?

154
00:07:44,731 --> 00:07:46,366
WHAT'S THE MOVIE?

155
00:07:46,366 --> 00:07:47,801
OH, IT'S A CLASSIC!

156
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:49,536
SURE

157
00:07:49,536 --> 00:07:52,272
HEY CHICAGO!

158
00:07:52,272 --> 00:07:53,340
[thump]

159
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:56,443
ANYTIME YOU WANT TO BUTT HEADS,
SUIT UP.

160
00:07:56,443 --> 00:07:59,079
WE CAN ALWAYS USE A COUPLE EXTRA
TACKLING DUMMIES.

161
00:07:59,079 --> 00:08:00,880
[all laugh]

162
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:02,382
BRING THEM BOOTS.

163
00:08:02,382 --> 00:08:04,451
LOOKS LIKE YOU HAVE ALL THE
DUMMIES YOU NEED.

164
00:08:04,451 --> 00:08:06,252
ICE!-- IF BRAINS
WERE DYNAMITE

165
00:08:06,252 --> 00:08:08,121
HE WOULDN'T HAVE ENOUGH
TO BLOW HIS NOSE.

166
00:08:08,121 --> 00:08:10,724
WELL, MAYBE I'LL SEE YOU FRIDAY?

167
00:08:10,724 --> 00:08:13,660
YAH. I'LL BRING THE JELLO MOLD.

168
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:22,635
I'LL DRIVE.

169
00:08:22,635 --> 00:08:24,604
RIGHT.

170
00:08:24,604 --> 00:08:31,111
[grunting]

171
00:08:34,714 --> 00:08:39,719
IF YOU THINK I'M CLOSIN' YOUR
DOOR FOR YOU, YOU CAN FORGET IT.

172
00:08:39,719 --> 00:08:41,654
(Jordy)
I HATE GRAIN.

173
00:08:41,654 --> 00:08:44,657
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE KID I SAW
THIS MOVIE WHERE THE ARMY

174
00:08:44,657 --> 00:08:47,727
WAS PUTTIN' NUCLEAR MISSILES
INSIDE THESE GRAIN SILOS.

175
00:08:47,727 --> 00:08:52,298
EVER SINCE THEN, THE HEARTLAND
HAS SEEMED SORT OF APOCALYPTIC.

176
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:57,303
DEATH AND DESTRUCTION
COULD BE LURKING

177
00:08:57,303 --> 00:08:59,839
INSIDE ANY ONE
OF THOSE BABIES.

178
00:09:02,675 --> 00:09:05,078
IT'S FOR ROADSIDE
 EMERGENCIES...

179
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:08,348
IT'S A BIBLE.

180
00:09:08,348 --> 00:09:11,418
PEACE WITH GOD?
(chuckles)

181
00:09:11,418 --> 00:09:13,720
WHO CAN BE
AT PEACE WITH GOD?

182
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:15,588
YOU CAN.

183
00:09:15,588 --> 00:09:18,591
AND I SUPPOSE YOU'RE
AT PEACE WITH GOD?

184
00:09:18,591 --> 00:09:21,928
YEAH. YEAH I AM.

185
00:09:24,998 --> 00:09:28,868
I'LL STICK WITH DEATH
AND DESTRUCTION.

186
00:09:28,868 --> 00:09:38,545
[engine roars]

187
00:09:38,545 --> 00:09:40,647
[engine rumbles]

188
00:09:40,647 --> 00:09:43,049
HOME SWEET HOME?

189
00:09:43,049 --> 00:09:45,752
'TILL MY BROTHER
CHANGES HIS MIND.

190
00:09:45,752 --> 00:09:48,221
WHAT ABOUT YOUR
 PARENTS?

191
00:09:48,221 --> 00:09:50,457
THEY'RE ON VACATION...

192
00:09:50,457 --> 00:09:52,926
FROM ME.

193
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:54,961
HEY, A BUNCH OF US ARE
 GETTIN' TOGETHER FRIDAY
 NIGHT

194
00:09:54,961 --> 00:09:56,663
TO WATCH A MOVIE.

195
00:09:56,663 --> 00:09:57,864
WHAT'S THE FLICK?

196
00:09:57,864 --> 00:09:59,732
LAWRENCE OF ARABIA.

197
00:09:59,732 --> 00:10:01,901
CAN'T YOU GUYS WATCH ANYTHING
FROM THIS CENTURY?

198
00:10:01,901 --> 00:10:04,537
HEY MIGHT BE A GREAT WAY TO
MEET PEOPLE FROM SCHOOL.

199
00:10:04,537 --> 00:10:06,539
YOU EVER HEARD OF CLC?

200
00:10:06,539 --> 00:10:08,108
ISN'T THAT
A GRUNGE BAND?

201
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:09,409
NO - CLC -

202
00:10:09,409 --> 00:10:11,344
A CAMPUS LIFE CLUB.

203
00:10:13,146 --> 00:10:15,515
THAT BE CONSIDERED
A PHILANTHROPIC CLUB?

204
00:10:15,515 --> 00:10:17,784
(male narrator on film) 
HE WENT TO ETHIOPIA

205
00:10:17,784 --> 00:10:20,153
AND SET UP A SMALL MISSION
FOR CHILDREN

206
00:10:20,153 --> 00:10:23,523
WHERE HE BECAME
LAWRENCE OF ETHIOPIA.

207
00:10:23,523 --> 00:10:24,891
HEY-- YOU MADE IT!

208
00:10:24,891 --> 00:10:26,759
YOU WANT TO START THIS OVER?

209
00:10:26,759 --> 00:10:28,561
IT'S GREAT,
 RIGHT UH-HUH.

210
00:10:32,832 --> 00:10:34,901
(Jordy)
WHERE IS EVERYBODY?

211
00:10:34,901 --> 00:10:36,903
(Wally)
LOOKS LIKE EVERYBODY'S HERE NOW.

212
00:10:36,903 --> 00:10:39,005
THIS IS ABOUT IT.

213
00:10:39,005 --> 00:10:41,274
THIS IS
   A BIBLE CLUB?

214
00:10:41,274 --> 00:10:43,943
2 GUYS?
AND A BIBLE.

215
00:10:43,943 --> 00:10:45,812
THINGS ARE GOING TO BE
DIFFERENT THIS YEAR.

216
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:47,480
YA, WE GOT FLYERS.

217
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,282
I'VE GOT ACTIVITIES PLANNED--

218
00:10:49,282 --> 00:10:50,683
A COUPLE
OF CONCERTS,

219
00:10:50,683 --> 00:10:52,652
A BILLY GRAHAM CRUSADE,
MOVIE NIGHT.

220
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:53,419
GREAT WALLY. LISTEN,

221
00:10:53,419 --> 00:10:54,621
I'VE GOT TO LEAVE,

222
00:10:54,621 --> 00:10:55,355
DO ME A FAVOR...

223
00:10:55,355 --> 00:10:56,322
DON'T WANT TO WATCH...

224
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:57,824
WE CAN
JUST HANG OUT--

225
00:10:57,824 --> 00:10:59,526
I'LL INTRODUCE YOU
TO EVERYBODY.

226
00:10:59,526 --> 00:11:01,194
THIS IS JIMMY.

227
00:11:01,194 --> 00:11:03,129
THIS IS ZIPPY.

228
00:11:03,129 --> 00:11:05,064
HERE COMES SOMEBODY ELSE.

229
00:11:05,064 --> 00:11:06,633
(Jordy)
HOPE YOU GOT ENOUGH CHAIRS.

230
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,001
SORRY I'M LATE-- HAD TO WALK MY
BIKE HERE,

231
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:09,269
I GOT A FLAT.

232
00:11:09,269 --> 00:11:10,537
HI.

233
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,640
HEY!

234
00:11:16,442 --> 00:11:18,778
I FEEL LIKE A BURGER.
 WANNA COME? YA!

235
00:11:18,778 --> 00:11:21,047
WAIT A MINUTE.
THIS MEETING'S NOT OVER YET!

236
00:11:21,047 --> 00:11:23,816
YOU'RE BUYING, RIGHT?
  SURE. OK, SOUNDS COOL.

237
00:11:23,816 --> 00:11:25,919
ALRIGHT, I GUESS WE
COULD END EARLY.

238
00:11:25,919 --> 00:11:27,954
WE'LL TAKE MY CAR.

239
00:11:27,954 --> 00:11:30,123
(Zippy)
WELL, I HAVE TO CALL MY MOTHER.

240
00:11:32,592 --> 00:11:34,327
OK, ZIPPY.

241
00:11:34,327 --> 00:11:36,429
(Wally)
WELCOME TO WESTBURY PARK--

242
00:11:36,429 --> 00:11:38,064
BADGER COUNTRY.

243
00:11:38,064 --> 00:11:39,933
PLEASE KEEP YOUR ARMS
AND LEGS INSIDE

244
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:41,301
HEY, MAN, WHAT YOU DOIN'

245
00:11:41,301 --> 00:11:42,001
(Wally)
SORRY!

246
00:11:42,001 --> 00:11:43,436
HEY BE CAREFUL WILL YA?

247
00:11:43,436 --> 00:11:45,305
SO THIS IS BADGERLAND?

248
00:11:45,305 --> 00:11:47,640
EXCUSE MOI, I MUST USE THE
BATHROOM!

249
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,442
THE BADGER IS A VERY
   VICIOUS ANIMAL

250
00:11:49,442 --> 00:11:51,477
I BETTER GO WITH HER.

251
00:11:55,848 --> 00:11:58,718
HEY MADGE!
HEY WALLY. HEY!

252
00:11:58,718 --> 00:12:00,587
WHAT ARE YOU
GUYS GONNA HAVE?

253
00:12:00,587 --> 00:12:02,221
GIVE US A COUPLE CHILI
 FRIES,

254
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:03,856
4 DOUBLE CHEESEBURGERS,

255
00:12:03,856 --> 00:12:06,125
3 COKES AND A RONDO.

256
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:07,894
COULD YOU MAKE MINE A
   CHOCOLATE SHAKE?

257
00:12:07,894 --> 00:12:12,165
CHOCOLATE SHAKE
HUH? ALRIGHT.

258
00:12:12,165 --> 00:12:14,200
SURE.
  THANKS.

259
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,935
SHE TALKED
 TO ME.

260
00:12:15,935 --> 00:12:17,403
JIMMIE, SHE'S OUR WAITRESS.

261
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:19,238
HEY, HOP IN THE FRONT WILL YA?

262
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:26,946
HEY FRESHMAN...
NICE CAR!

263
00:12:26,946 --> 00:12:28,281
THANKS. YOU TOO.

264
00:12:28,281 --> 00:12:30,984
YOUR CAR I MEAN.
   ALLOW ME.

265
00:12:30,984 --> 00:12:34,120
OOH! WHAT A GENTLEMAN.

266
00:12:35,321 --> 00:12:39,125
HOW CUTE.
   HE BLUSHED.

267
00:12:40,393 --> 00:12:42,095
HEY! COMIN' THROUGH!
AAAAAHH!!

268
00:12:42,095 --> 00:12:43,596
[splat]

269
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:45,832
OH MY GOSH, YOU OK?

270
00:12:45,832 --> 00:12:49,002
NICE MOVE MORON!
   THAT WAS OUR
   DINNER.

271
00:12:49,002 --> 00:12:50,637
IT'S NO
PROBLEM REALLY.

272
00:12:50,637 --> 00:12:52,071
HELP HER UP,
   PUNK!

273
00:12:52,071 --> 00:12:53,873
IT'S OK, I'LL GET SOMEBODY
  TO CLEAN THIS UP.

274
00:12:53,873 --> 00:12:56,042
THE PUNK WILL CLEAN
 IT UP,

275
00:12:56,042 --> 00:12:57,377
WON'T YOU PUNK?

276
00:12:57,377 --> 00:12:58,911
(Wally)
LOOK IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

277
00:12:58,911 --> 00:13:00,580
WE'LL PAY FOR IT.

278
00:13:00,580 --> 00:13:01,981
OH, YOU WILL.

279
00:13:01,981 --> 00:13:04,684
RIGHT AFTER YOU AND YOUR
  FRIEND LICK THIS UP.

280
00:13:04,684 --> 00:13:06,452
(Wally)
I SAID WE'D PAY FOR IT.

281
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,627
WHAT'S WRONG WITH
 YOU FISH,

282
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,062
YOU GOT A PROBLEM
 WITH THAT?

283
00:13:16,062 --> 00:13:18,731
WHAT'S THE MATTER,
   CAN'T YOU TALK

284
00:13:18,731 --> 00:13:20,767
I CAN'T WALK.
   WHAT?

285
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:23,069
I CAN'T WALK!

286
00:13:23,069 --> 00:13:26,205
BIF, MAN-- THE GUY'S
   A GIMP. (laughing)

287
00:13:26,205 --> 00:13:28,408
(Jordy)
 PUT HIM DOWN!

288
00:13:28,408 --> 00:13:30,576
OOF!

289
00:13:30,576 --> 00:13:32,945
HOW'S WAS I S'POSE TO
   KNOW HE WAS A CRIPPLE.

290
00:13:32,945 --> 00:13:34,914
I DIDN'T SEE A SIGN OR NOTHIN'.

291
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:36,849
C'MON MAN.
 LET'S SPLIT.

292
00:13:39,419 --> 00:13:42,355
HEY WHAT ARE YOU
 LOOKING AT?

293
00:13:43,423 --> 00:13:46,526
YEAH. THAT'S WHAT I
 THOUGHT.

294
00:13:46,526 --> 00:13:48,995
HEY BUZZ, CHECK
   IT OUT.

295
00:13:48,995 --> 00:13:53,366
A GIMP... A
 SHRIMP... AND A
 WIMP. (laughing)

296
00:13:53,366 --> 00:13:56,102
[thud... bloof]

297
00:13:56,102 --> 00:13:59,572
[everyone yelling]

298
00:13:59,572 --> 00:14:02,608
AAAAAHHHH!!... [THUD!]

299
00:14:02,608 --> 00:14:04,210
YAAAAAHHHHH!!!!... OOF!

300
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:06,746
[splat!]

301
00:14:06,746 --> 00:14:09,315
(Pam) YOU OK?

302
00:14:09,315 --> 00:14:11,250
[whoosh]

303
00:14:12,618 --> 00:14:13,786
[whack]

304
00:14:13,786 --> 00:14:15,054
[whoosh]

305
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:17,256
[whack]

306
00:14:17,256 --> 00:14:19,559
AAAAAH!!... OH!

307
00:14:19,559 --> 00:14:20,960
[everyone yelling]

308
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:22,328
KNOCK IT OFF!!

309
00:14:23,763 --> 00:14:25,598
GET IN THE
CAR NOW!!

310
00:14:25,598 --> 00:14:27,266
(Pam)
C'MON!

311
00:14:28,901 --> 00:14:30,703
SORRY JORDY.
   YOU OKAY?

312
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:33,306
WHEN DO WE PLAY THOSE
GUYS?

313
00:14:33,306 --> 00:14:35,775
[screech!!]

314
00:14:35,775 --> 00:14:37,110
[smash!!]

315
00:14:44,917 --> 00:14:47,687
(Ice)
WHAT CHANGED YOUR MIND, CHICAGO?

316
00:14:47,687 --> 00:14:49,489
(Jordy)
 BIBLE STUDY.

317
00:14:51,657 --> 00:14:54,260
COACH?

318
00:14:54,260 --> 00:14:56,429
REMBRANDT...

319
00:14:56,429 --> 00:14:58,765
START ON DEFENSE.

320
00:14:58,765 --> 00:15:00,767
I'M A WIDE RECEIVER.

321
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:04,003
OH... PLEASE DON'T
PUNCH ME, REMBRANDT.

322
00:15:04,003 --> 00:15:06,405
LET'S RUN
THE OFFENSE...

323
00:15:08,474 --> 00:15:11,244
YOU TOO!

324
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:16,048
ALRIGHT, GENTLEMEN!

325
00:15:16,048 --> 00:15:19,185
TODAY WE HAVE TO
MAKE A DECISION.

326
00:15:19,185 --> 00:15:21,254
WHO ARE YOU
GOING TO FOLLOW?

327
00:15:21,254 --> 00:15:23,890
WHO ARE YOU
GOING TO PLAY FOR?

328
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:27,026
NOW, TO PLAY FOR ME, YOU HAVE TO
FOLLOW MY RULES.

329
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:28,594
REMBRANDT!!

330
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:30,329
THIS IS A TEAM--

331
00:15:30,329 --> 00:15:31,898
YOU START DOING YOUR OWN THING,

332
00:15:31,898 --> 00:15:33,599
AND YOU'LL FIND YOURSELF HURT,
BENCHED OR BOTH!

333
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:35,401
YOU GOT IT?

334
00:15:35,401 --> 00:15:37,203
ALL RIGHT TEAM,

335
00:15:37,203 --> 00:15:39,438
EVERYBODY FOLLOW REMBRANDT--

336
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:41,908
5 LAPS AROUND THE FIELD!

337
00:15:41,908 --> 00:15:46,112
(many voices)
   ALRIGHT! C'MON, LET'S GO!

338
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:49,916
[bird chirps]

339
00:15:54,887 --> 00:15:57,223
HEY, YOU!
HEY!

340
00:15:57,223 --> 00:15:58,991
FOOTBALL, HUH?
YEAH.

341
00:15:58,991 --> 00:16:00,059
WHERE ARE
YOU HEADED?

342
00:16:00,059 --> 00:16:01,260
HOMECOMING COMMITTEE.

343
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:03,062
I THOUGHT MAYBE WE COULD DO
 SOMETHIN'...

344
00:16:03,062 --> 00:16:05,731
HEY YOU GUYS COMING
TO THE MEETING?

345
00:16:05,731 --> 00:16:07,767
AH... THINKING
   ABOUT IT.

346
00:16:07,767 --> 00:16:09,035
I THOUGHT WE'D
ALL GRAB SOMETHIN'

347
00:16:09,035 --> 00:16:11,103
AT TOLI'S AFTERWARDS...
CELEBRATE.

348
00:16:11,103 --> 00:16:12,772
YEAH. LET'S GO
   BACK TO
   BADGERLAND.

349
00:16:12,772 --> 00:16:14,240
WHAT ARE WE
   CELEBRATING?

350
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:16,275
OH, AH, HA, HA, HA!

351
00:16:17,677 --> 00:16:19,779
(Pam)
OK, C'MON STUDENT COUNCIL
COME TO ORDER PLEASE!

352
00:16:19,779 --> 00:16:21,447
WE HAVE 4 ENTRIES

353
00:16:21,447 --> 00:16:24,217
FOR THIS YEAR'S SENIOR
HOMECOMING FLOAT, SO UM...

354
00:16:24,217 --> 00:16:25,852
BARRY, WHY DON'T
WE START WITH YOU.

355
00:16:25,852 --> 00:16:29,288
WELL, WE STILL HAVE THE FLOAT
FROM LAST YEAR.

356
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:31,524
SHEERAH?

357
00:16:31,524 --> 00:16:35,728
I ENVISION A
30-FOOT AMAZONIAN GODDESS

358
00:16:35,728 --> 00:16:40,433
A HARBINGER ARCHETYPE OF THE
SHE-WOMAN EARTH MOTHER.

359
00:16:40,433 --> 00:16:42,468
RIGHT ON!

360
00:16:42,468 --> 00:16:46,639
OK... I GET MY DAD'S
'58 CONVERTIBLE.

361
00:16:46,639 --> 00:16:49,876
WE PLASTER CHEERLEADERS
ALL OVER IT...

362
00:16:51,577 --> 00:16:53,212
I DRIVE.

363
00:16:53,212 --> 00:16:54,714
YEAH!!

364
00:16:54,714 --> 00:16:58,117
OW, OW, OOOOH!

365
00:17:05,091 --> 00:17:21,040
♪ [suspenseful strings] ♪

366
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:26,946
[small electric motor whirs]

367
00:17:26,946 --> 00:17:28,014
[whoosh!]

368
00:17:28,014 --> 00:17:29,348
GRRRR!

369
00:17:29,348 --> 00:17:39,425
[cheering & clapping]

370
00:17:52,405 --> 00:17:55,575
(girls)
WALLY, THAT WAS AWESOME!
HOW DID YOU DO IT?

371
00:17:58,344 --> 00:18:02,782
NOW THIS COULD REALLY
BOOST SCHOOL SPIRIT.

372
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:07,520
I THOUGHT WE WERE
GOING TO TOLI'S.

373
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:10,323
JUST WANTED YOU A MINUTE
   TO MYSELF.

374
00:18:10,323 --> 00:18:12,692
YOU WANT TO
WALK THEN?

375
00:18:14,627 --> 00:18:16,495
I THOUGHT WE COULD
   JUST SIT.

376
00:18:16,495 --> 00:18:18,097
TALK.

377
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:20,266
OKAY.

378
00:18:24,804 --> 00:18:26,906
UM...

379
00:18:26,906 --> 00:18:28,641
WE BETTER GO--
I MEAN, WALLY'S...

380
00:18:28,641 --> 00:18:31,010
WALLY'S A BIG BOY.

381
00:18:31,010 --> 00:18:33,412
LET'S FINISH OUR
   CONVERSATION.

382
00:18:38,417 --> 00:18:44,490
♪ [melancholy flute] ♪

383
00:18:44,490 --> 00:18:50,029
[flute & strings]

384
00:18:53,099 --> 00:18:55,668
WHAT'S THE
   MATTER?

385
00:19:00,172 --> 00:19:03,843
JORDY, I REALLY
LIKE YOU.

386
00:19:08,547 --> 00:19:12,485
BUT, MAYBE YOU SHOULD JUST
TAKE ME HOME.

387
00:19:12,485 --> 00:19:14,453
(sighs)

388
00:19:14,453 --> 00:19:18,090
WAIT!

389
00:19:18,090 --> 00:19:20,726
CHANGE YOUR MIND?

390
00:19:24,764 --> 00:19:27,900
I'VE SET CERTAIN
BOUNDARIES, JORDY.

391
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:31,037
SO, THIS IS ABOUT
 YOUR RELIGION.

392
00:19:31,037 --> 00:19:32,605
NO, I JUST DON'T WANT
TO GET HURT.

393
00:19:32,605 --> 00:19:34,640
IT'S NOT--

394
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:37,476
IT'S ABOUT THIS
RELATIONSHIP I HAVE...

395
00:19:37,476 --> 00:19:39,345
WITH WALLY?

396
00:19:39,345 --> 00:19:44,383
WITH GOD.

397
00:19:44,383 --> 00:19:47,086
GOD DOESN'T WANT US
   TO HAVE ANY FUN?

398
00:19:47,086 --> 00:19:48,621
NO, HE DOES, BUT

399
00:19:48,621 --> 00:19:50,956
HE JUST CARES ABOUT US
SO MUCH THAT

400
00:19:50,956 --> 00:19:53,359
HE DOESN'T WANT TO SEE US
BE HURT

401
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:56,195
OR, YOU KNOW,
MESS THINGS UP,

402
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:57,930
AND EITHER DO I.

403
00:19:57,930 --> 00:19:59,698
YOU REALLY BELIEVE
   ALL THAT STUFF?

404
00:19:59,698 --> 00:20:03,469
YES. AND, YOU KNOW,
BELIEVING ISN'T SOMETHING

405
00:20:03,469 --> 00:20:05,404
THAT YOU JUST DO
IN YOUR MIND -

406
00:20:05,404 --> 00:20:07,473
IN YOUR HEAD -

407
00:20:07,473 --> 00:20:09,875
I MEAN, HE'S IN MY HEART.

408
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:12,445
AND IT'S SOMETHING YOU DO
WITH YOUR WHOLE BODY,

409
00:20:12,445 --> 00:20:16,916
AND YOUR HEART, AND YOUR MIND,
AND YOUR EVERYTHING.

410
00:20:16,916 --> 00:20:19,285
AND SOMETIMES THAT'S
REALLY HARD,

411
00:20:19,285 --> 00:20:22,455
BUT, I MEAN, IT'S
A DECISION I'VE MADE,

412
00:20:22,455 --> 00:20:26,692
AND IT'S SOMETHING THAT
I WANT TO LIVE BY.

413
00:20:26,692 --> 00:20:30,362
THAT'S WHY I WON'T
SWIM OUT THAT FAR...

414
00:20:30,362 --> 00:20:34,433
I WANT US TO STAY
CLOSE TO SHORE.

415
00:20:38,370 --> 00:20:41,874
WELL MAYBE YOU BETTER
   JUST STAY ON THE
   BEACH.

416
00:20:44,210 --> 00:20:47,179
ALL RIGHT DEFENSE,
GET IN THERE.

417
00:20:47,179 --> 00:20:58,023
[tense music,
crowd cheering]

418
00:20:58,023 --> 00:21:00,559
WELL, I HOPE THEY
PULL SOMETHING OUT.

419
00:21:00,559 --> 00:21:02,962
READY... SET...

420
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:08,834
(male announcer) 
FIRST DOWN, BALL IS ON THE...

421
00:21:08,834 --> 00:21:10,603
HUT ONE!

422
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:14,140
OOF... [grunting]

423
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,542
(announcer) 
INTERCEPTED!

424
00:21:16,542 --> 00:21:18,778
BY NUMBER 20, JORDY REMBRANDT.

425
00:21:18,778 --> 00:21:20,880
HE'S AT THE 50,

426
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,515
HE'S AT THE 40,

427
00:21:22,515 --> 00:21:24,617
HE COULD GO ALL THE WAY.

428
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:26,485
[loud screaming & cheering]

429
00:21:26,485 --> 00:21:28,888
TOUCHDOWN!

430
00:21:28,888 --> 00:21:36,295
♪ [triumphant orchestral
brass & cymbals] ♪

431
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:47,406
♪    ♪

432
00:21:47,406 --> 00:21:49,108
♪ [fuzz rock guitar] ♪

433
00:21:49,108 --> 00:21:51,076
(Wally)
IS THAT A BEER?

434
00:21:51,076 --> 00:21:53,612
(Pam)
I'M JUST HOLDING IT.

435
00:21:53,612 --> 00:21:55,481
(Wally)
YOU'RE NOT SETTING A VERY GOOD
EXAMPLE HERE.

436
00:21:55,481 --> 00:21:57,049
EXAMPLE, WALLY?

437
00:21:57,049 --> 00:21:59,018
NOBODY EVEN KNOWS WE EXIST.

438
00:21:59,018 --> 00:22:01,020
HEY, CROWDER,
HOW 'BOUT A BREW?

439
00:22:01,020 --> 00:22:02,354
NO THANKS BRO'...

440
00:22:02,354 --> 00:22:05,057
ONE BREW AND
 I MIGHT LOSE CONTROL--

441
00:22:05,057 --> 00:22:06,926
START DANCING
 ON THE TABLE.

442
00:22:08,427 --> 00:22:10,429
(Ice)
I WANTED YOU
TO GET ME ONE.

443
00:22:10,429 --> 00:22:12,665
OH. HOW ABOUT
A PEPSI?

444
00:22:12,665 --> 00:22:14,767
WOULDN'T WANT YOU TO
 VIOLATE YOUR TRAINING RULES.

445
00:22:14,767 --> 00:22:16,535
WHERE'S JORDY?

446
00:22:16,535 --> 00:22:18,504
DISAPPEARED.

447
00:22:18,504 --> 00:22:22,441
♪    ♪

448
00:22:22,441 --> 00:22:24,610
CAN I GET
YOU ANYTHING?

449
00:22:24,610 --> 00:22:29,848
[fuzz rock guitar
& people chattering]

450
00:22:29,848 --> 00:22:31,817
(Wally)
GUESS NOT.

451
00:22:31,817 --> 00:22:38,557
♪    ♪

452
00:22:38,557 --> 00:22:40,926
[zip... zip]

453
00:22:40,926 --> 00:22:46,599
[cheering]

454
00:22:46,599 --> 00:22:49,068
FIRE IN THE HOLE!

455
00:22:49,068 --> 00:22:56,775
[cheering]

456
00:22:56,775 --> 00:22:58,944
[whoosh!]

457
00:22:58,944 --> 00:23:01,513
[cheering]

458
00:23:03,949 --> 00:23:06,118
GREAT JOB, JORDY!
   THANKS.

459
00:23:06,118 --> 00:23:07,453
PIZZA TIME!

460
00:23:07,453 --> 00:23:08,954
ARE YOU GOING?

461
00:23:08,954 --> 00:23:10,589
YEAH. LET'S ALL GO.

462
00:23:10,589 --> 00:23:12,858
(Pam) UH, GUYS... WHAT ABOUT US?

463
00:23:12,858 --> 00:23:14,793
WALLY'S STILL WORKING ON
 THE THING.

464
00:23:14,793 --> 00:23:19,465
WELL YOU GUYS CAN FOLLOW US
LATER IN WALLY'S CAR.

465
00:23:19,465 --> 00:23:23,235
YEAH, BUT SEE, WE CAME
   WITH JORDY.

466
00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:25,604
MICHELLE--
RIDE WITH ME?

467
00:23:25,604 --> 00:23:27,806
JORDY SAID HE'D TAKE ME.

468
00:23:27,806 --> 00:23:31,076
MICHELLE CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

469
00:23:31,076 --> 00:23:34,013
(other students)
WHO'S GOT THE KEYS TO MY TRUCK?
 MIKE HAS THEM.

470
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:39,852
WHAT?
WHAT IS IT?

471
00:23:39,852 --> 00:23:41,620
I WAS JUST WONDERING.

472
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:43,188
IF YOU WEREN'T ALREADY
   GOING TO HOMECOMING,

473
00:23:43,188 --> 00:23:44,757
I WAS THINKING MAYBE WE
 COULD...

474
00:23:44,757 --> 00:23:45,958
THAT'S REALLY SWEET ICE

475
00:23:45,958 --> 00:23:47,826
BUT I'VE ALREADY
BEEN ASKED.

476
00:23:47,826 --> 00:23:50,129
SORRY.

477
00:23:50,129 --> 00:23:52,464
JORDY?

478
00:23:55,301 --> 00:23:57,936
JORDY?
 RIGHT.

479
00:23:57,936 --> 00:24:00,306
I CAN COME BACK
   FOR YOU GUYS.

480
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:10,215
(sighs) BOYS...

481
00:24:10,215 --> 00:24:11,917
WHY ARE THEY
 SO STUPID?

482
00:24:11,917 --> 00:24:13,052
HEY WATCH IT,

483
00:24:13,052 --> 00:24:14,620
