00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:16,555
NOT YOU, WALLY, I DON'T
  CONSIDER YOU ONE OF THEM.

485
00:24:16,555 --> 00:24:18,057
OH, THANKS.

486
00:24:18,057 --> 00:24:19,692
SHUT UP. YOU KNOW WHAT I
  MEAN.

487
00:24:19,692 --> 00:24:21,360
IT'S JUST NOT FAIR.

488
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:22,594
WHAT?

489
00:24:22,594 --> 00:24:23,729
THIS WHOLE
 CHRISTIAN THING,

490
00:24:23,729 --> 00:24:25,164
YOU KNOW, ALWAYS HAVING

491
00:24:25,164 --> 00:24:26,999
TO BE THIS GOOD LITTLE
   GIRL ALL THE TIME.

492
00:24:26,999 --> 00:24:28,667
AND THINGS WOULD BE DIFFERENT
IF YOU WEREN'T?

493
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:30,436
WHY DO I HAVE TO LIKE HIM?

494
00:24:30,436 --> 00:24:33,138
WHY CAN'T I LIKE SOMEBODY
  LIKE YOU?

495
00:24:35,374 --> 00:24:37,576
(Wally)
IT'S EASY DOING WHAT EVERYBODY
ELSE IS DOING.

496
00:24:37,576 --> 00:24:39,745
EVERYONE'S GOTTA SET BOUNDARIES.

497
00:24:39,745 --> 00:24:42,581
BOUNDARIES AREN'T
NECESSARILY BAD.

498
00:24:42,581 --> 00:24:44,283
REMEMBER COLORING BOOKS,
AS A KID?

499
00:24:44,283 --> 00:24:45,951
(Pam)
YEAH. WHAT ABOUT EM?

500
00:24:45,951 --> 00:24:47,286
(Wally)
IN MY FAMILY
WE USED TO HAVE RACES

501
00:24:47,286 --> 00:24:49,154
TO SEE WHO COULD FINISH A
COLORING BOOK FIRST.

502
00:24:49,154 --> 00:24:51,557
I ALWAYS WON.

503
00:24:51,557 --> 00:24:53,959
BUT THERE WAS THIS LITTLE GIRL
WHO LIVED ACROSS THE STREET,

504
00:24:53,959 --> 00:24:55,594
SHE WOULDN'T RACE...

505
00:24:55,594 --> 00:24:57,463
REFUSED! (Pam chuckles)

506
00:24:57,463 --> 00:25:00,165
SHE'D SPEND A WHOLE WEEK
ON ONE PAGE!

507
00:25:00,165 --> 00:25:04,703
(Pam)
SO... MAYBE HER PARENTS WOULDN'T
BUY HER NEW BOOKS?

508
00:25:04,703 --> 00:25:06,538
NO. THAT
WASN'T IT.

509
00:25:06,538 --> 00:25:08,774
SHE WAS TAKING HER TIME
TO MAKE THEM SPECIAL.

510
00:25:08,774 --> 00:25:11,643
AND THEY WERE, BECAUSE
SHE TOOK HER TIME.

511
00:25:11,643 --> 00:25:13,946
I WAS ALL OVER THE PLACE--

512
00:25:13,946 --> 00:25:16,482
WASTIN' TREES
WHILE SHE WAS MAKING ART.

513
00:25:16,482 --> 00:25:19,318
PICTURES THAT WOULD LAST-- 
KEEPERS.

514
00:25:19,318 --> 00:25:22,087
YOU KNOW WHERE
THAT GIRL IS TODAY?

515
00:25:22,087 --> 00:25:24,089
UH, THERAPY?

516
00:25:24,089 --> 00:25:28,193
NO, SHE'S BUILDING FLOATS
AT MORRIS HIGH.

517
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:32,331
SHE'S STAYING INSIDE THE LINES,
TAKING HER TIME.

518
00:25:32,331 --> 00:25:37,102
SHE'S MAKING SOMETHING BEAUTIFUL
OUT OF HER LIFE.

519
00:25:37,102 --> 00:25:40,105
SOMETIMES, IT'S REAL
   HARD,YOU KNOW.

520
00:25:40,105 --> 00:25:45,210
YEAH... IT'S A FIGHT
TO DO WHAT'S RIGHT.

521
00:25:45,210 --> 00:25:50,449
BUT GOD NEVER TESTS US BEYOND
WHAT WE'RE ABLE TO ENDURE.

522
00:25:50,449 --> 00:25:53,352
WELL. HERE WE ARE...

523
00:25:53,352 --> 00:25:55,921
HERE WE ARE.

524
00:25:57,022 --> 00:25:59,425
WELL... GOODNIGHT.

525
00:25:59,425 --> 00:26:01,427
WAIT, WALLY?

526
00:26:01,427 --> 00:26:04,496
WHAT DID YOU DO WITH
 THOSE PICTURES

527
00:26:04,496 --> 00:26:06,131
WHERE YOU WENT OUTSIDE
 OF THE LINES?

528
00:26:06,131 --> 00:26:10,235
GOD HAS A WAY OF TAKING
EVEN MY WORST MISTAKES

529
00:26:10,235 --> 00:26:12,938
AND MAKING SOMETHING GOOD
OUT OF THEM.

530
00:26:12,938 --> 00:26:15,774
HIS GRACE IS...

531
00:26:15,774 --> 00:26:19,278
IT'S A NEW COLORING BOOK,
Y'KNOW?

532
00:26:21,814 --> 00:26:24,750
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
 HOW GREAT YOU ARE?

533
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:35,160
[splashing of rain,
orchestral music]

534
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:37,563
I'VE NEVER KISSED
ANYONE BEFORE--

535
00:26:37,563 --> 00:26:40,098
'CEPT MAYBE
THOSE TREE FROGS.

536
00:26:40,098 --> 00:26:42,634
OH...

537
00:26:42,634 --> 00:26:46,805
WELL... GOODNIGHT.

538
00:26:51,276 --> 00:26:53,912
YOU'RE A KEEPER,
   WALLY CROWDER...

539
00:26:56,348 --> 00:26:58,450
YOU'RE A KEEPER!

540
00:27:00,319 --> 00:27:03,021
[dog barks]

541
00:27:03,021 --> 00:27:05,190
[barking louder]

542
00:27:05,190 --> 00:27:14,333
[suspenseful music]

543
00:27:14,333 --> 00:27:25,077
[rushing sounds]

544
00:27:25,077 --> 00:27:40,659
[crackling]

545
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:42,895
IT'S TOAST, MAN!!

546
00:27:42,895 --> 00:27:45,430
(Wags)
THEY JUST BURNED OUR FLOAT.

547
00:27:45,430 --> 00:27:49,334
(Moto)
IT'S TOAST MAN.
IT'S TOAST.

548
00:27:49,334 --> 00:27:51,003
(Wags)
I SAY WE KILL 'EM.

549
00:27:51,003 --> 00:27:52,738
DEATH TO BADGERS!

550
00:27:52,738 --> 00:27:55,941
(all chanting)
KILL, KILL, KILL, KILL!

551
00:27:55,941 --> 00:27:58,544
(Moto)
IT'S TOAST, IT'S TOAST, MAN!!

552
00:27:58,544 --> 00:28:02,381
(all chanting)
KILL, KILL, KILL, KILL!

553
00:28:02,381 --> 00:28:08,720
♪ (heavy strings) ♪

554
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:19,298
♪    ♪

555
00:28:25,270 --> 00:28:28,640
HEY, NICE GAME.

556
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:29,975
I STEPPED OUT OF BOUNDS.

557
00:28:29,975 --> 00:28:31,877
HEY WE STILL WON.

558
00:28:31,877 --> 00:28:34,146
LISTEN. SOME OF THE GUYS
   ARE GETTING TOGETHER
   TONIGHT,

559
00:28:34,146 --> 00:28:35,414
I THOUGHT MAYBE WE
   COULD...

560
00:28:35,414 --> 00:28:36,515
UH, I CAN'T.

561
00:28:36,515 --> 00:28:37,816
IT'S CROWDER'S BIRTHDAY.
I GOTTA BE THERE.

562
00:28:37,816 --> 00:28:39,985
WHADDYA STILL HANGING AROUND
THAT LOSER FOR?

563
00:28:39,985 --> 00:28:41,520
WALLY'S A FRIEND.

564
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:42,821
WELL, WE'RE YOUR TEAMMATES.

565
00:28:42,821 --> 00:28:44,656
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BE
DEPENDING ON CROWDER

566
00:28:44,656 --> 00:28:46,925
TO BE PUSHING 200 POUNDS OF
BADGER AROUND THE FIELD

567
00:28:46,925 --> 00:28:48,794
SO YOU CAN MAKE A TOUCHDOWN.

568
00:28:50,862 --> 00:28:53,699
WE'RE LAYING A BLOCK
TONIGHT.

569
00:28:53,699 --> 00:28:55,500
I'LL SEE YOU THERE.

570
00:29:03,208 --> 00:29:07,012
[Wally blowing loudly]

571
00:29:07,012 --> 00:29:09,915
I DON'T KNOW WHAT COULD HAVE
HAPPENED TO HIM.

572
00:29:09,915 --> 00:29:12,184
(Jimmy)
HE COULD'VE FORGOT.

573
00:29:12,184 --> 00:29:13,952
SORRY, WALLY.

574
00:29:13,952 --> 00:29:15,887
OR MAYBE HE'S WITH MICHELLE.

575
00:29:15,887 --> 00:29:18,223
I'D FORGET MY OWN BIRTHDAY--

576
00:29:18,223 --> 00:29:20,859
JIMMY...
WE GET THE POINT, ALRIGHT?

577
00:29:20,859 --> 00:29:23,462
HEY. IT'S ONLY A BIRTHDAY.

578
00:29:26,164 --> 00:29:28,700
(Jordy)
WESTBURY PARK?

579
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:31,236
(Ice)
WE THOUGHT WE'D STOP AND PICK UP
SOMETHING TO EAT.

580
00:29:31,236 --> 00:29:33,672
(Wags)
YEAH, WHAT DOES BADGER TASTE
LIKE ANYWAY?

581
00:29:33,672 --> 00:29:35,607
(Jordy)
OH NO. WAIT, YOU GUYS.

582
00:29:35,607 --> 00:29:37,476
(Ice)
C'MON, IT'S NEVER BEEN DONE.

583
00:29:37,476 --> 00:29:38,610
WON'T OUR FLOAT LOOK GOOD

584
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:40,979
BEING PULLED BY A LIVE BADGER.
(chuckles)

585
00:29:43,682 --> 00:29:50,188
♪ [drums & heavy strings] ♪

586
00:29:50,188 --> 00:29:53,558
(Jordy)
GOT IT. LET'S GO!

587
00:29:53,558 --> 00:29:55,494
♪    ♪

588
00:29:55,494 --> 00:29:57,429
(Moto)
WE'RE IN!

589
00:29:57,429 --> 00:30:06,638
♪    ♪

590
00:30:06,638 --> 00:30:31,329
[deep breathing]

591
00:30:31,329 --> 00:30:42,941
♪    ♪

592
00:30:42,941 --> 00:30:46,611
GOT IT!
LET'S GO.

593
00:30:46,611 --> 00:30:47,979
GRRRRR!

594
00:30:47,979 --> 00:30:56,888
[all screaming,
   growls]

595
00:30:58,724 --> 00:31:00,525
IT'S OUT!!

596
00:31:00,525 --> 00:31:03,995
AHH!! IT'S GOT MY FLASHLIGHT.

597
00:31:03,995 --> 00:31:06,298
[screaming]

598
00:31:06,298 --> 00:31:09,534
AAHHH!! IT'S GOT MY SHOE!

599
00:31:09,534 --> 00:31:11,903
(Floater)
DUDES! RUN FOR YOUR LIVES!!

600
00:31:11,903 --> 00:31:14,806
[screaming]

601
00:31:14,806 --> 00:31:16,408
(Moto)
THAT THING'S CRAZY!

602
00:31:17,242 --> 00:31:19,711
(Wags)
WE GOT NOTHIN'!

603
00:31:19,711 --> 00:31:21,813
(Floater)
DUDE, IT SHREDDED YOUR PANTS!

604
00:31:21,813 --> 00:31:24,416
(Wags)
MY PANTS? LOOK AT MY SHOE!

605
00:31:24,416 --> 00:31:28,987
[guys chattering]

606
00:31:28,987 --> 00:31:31,590
GRRRRRR!!

607
00:31:31,590 --> 00:31:42,334
♪    ♪

608
00:31:42,334 --> 00:31:52,377
[music becomes tenser]

609
00:31:52,377 --> 00:31:56,181
(Jordy)
ONE, 2, 3.

610
00:31:56,181 --> 00:32:04,322
[all grunting]

611
00:32:04,322 --> 00:32:08,493
♪     ♪

612
00:32:08,493 --> 00:32:14,199
♪ [intensity builds] ♪

613
00:32:14,199 --> 00:32:16,201
[all yelling]

614
00:32:16,201 --> 00:32:17,869
♪   ♪

615
00:32:17,869 --> 00:32:21,006
[boom... BLAM!!]

616
00:32:21,006 --> 00:32:24,075
[all yelling]

617
00:32:24,075 --> 00:32:26,011
IT'S TOAST GUYS!

618
00:32:26,011 --> 00:32:28,547
[yelling]

619
00:32:28,547 --> 00:32:31,316
YES! YES! AW THAT
   WAS BEAUTIFUL MAN!

620
00:32:31,316 --> 00:32:33,552
YES! YEAH!...

621
00:32:33,552 --> 00:32:35,887
YES!!

622
00:32:35,887 --> 00:32:38,056
[crackling]

623
00:32:38,056 --> 00:32:40,892
AWESOME DUDE,
   TOTALLY AWESOME!

624
00:32:40,892 --> 00:32:43,728
♪ [jazz clarinet & strings] ♪

625
00:32:43,728 --> 00:32:55,540
♪  ♪

626
00:32:55,540 --> 00:32:57,542
REMBRANDT!

627
00:32:57,542 --> 00:32:59,144
SEE YOU
 IN MY OFFICE.

628
00:33:10,288 --> 00:33:13,491
JORDY, THIS
IS OFFICER STAVERMAN

629
00:33:13,491 --> 00:33:15,594
OF THE MORRIS
POLICE FORCE.

630
00:33:15,594 --> 00:33:17,395
I ASKED WALLY
TO BE HERE BECAUSE

631
00:33:17,395 --> 00:33:19,664
HE'S PRESIDENT
OF THE STUDENT GOVERNMENT,

632
00:33:19,664 --> 00:33:22,133
AND THIS DOES INVOLVE
THE ENTIRE STUDENT BODY.

633
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:24,135
BUT OFFICER STAVERMAN WOULD LIKE

634
00:33:24,135 --> 00:33:26,137
TO ASK YOU A FEW QUESTIONS.

635
00:33:26,137 --> 00:33:27,706
OKAY.

636
00:33:27,706 --> 00:33:30,842
SO, JORDY, CAN YOU TELL US WHERE
YOU WERE LAST NIGHT?

637
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:34,279
WELL, THERE WAS A PARTY LAST
NIGHT...

638
00:33:34,279 --> 00:33:38,116
BUT I STAYED HOME. STUDYING.

639
00:33:38,116 --> 00:33:41,019
STUDYING.

640
00:33:41,019 --> 00:33:44,089
YOU KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT THAT
WESTBURY PARK BOOSTER BUS

641
00:33:44,089 --> 00:33:45,957
THAT BLEW ITSELF UP?

642
00:33:45,957 --> 00:33:47,993
NO, WAS ANYBODY HURT?

643
00:33:47,993 --> 00:33:50,228
SO FAR, SO GOOD.

644
00:33:50,228 --> 00:33:53,298
LOOKS LIKE IT WAS JUST A PRANK
THAT WENT A LITTLE AWRY.

645
00:33:53,298 --> 00:33:57,435
ALTHOUGH I DO UNDERSTAND THAT
THERE IS A BOUNTY OUT.

646
00:33:59,471 --> 00:34:02,107
AM I BEING CHARGED WITH
SOMETHING?

647
00:34:02,107 --> 00:34:04,009
'CAUSE I KNOW MY RIGHTS.

648
00:34:04,009 --> 00:34:06,478
OH, I'M SURE YOU DO.

649
00:34:06,478 --> 00:34:08,847
THE POLICE ARE LOOKING
FOR ANY INFORMATION

650
00:34:08,847 --> 00:34:12,984
THAT MIGHT HELP THEM FIND THE
KID OR KIDS WHO DID THIS.

651
00:34:12,984 --> 00:34:15,520
WHAT MAKES YOU
THINK IT WAS US?

652
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:17,322
WE DON'T KNOW WHO DID IT JORDY.

653
00:34:17,322 --> 00:34:19,424
BUT UNFORTUNATELY, THERE'S A
WHOLE SCHOOL

654
00:34:19,424 --> 00:34:22,560
FULL OF KIDS OVER AT WESTBURY
PARK WHO THINK THEY DO.

655
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:25,030
NOW WE'RE JUST TRYING TO END
THIS WHOLE THING

656
00:34:25,030 --> 00:34:26,431
RIGHT HERE AND NOW

657
00:34:26,431 --> 00:34:28,900
BEFORE SOMEBODY DOES GET HURT.

658
00:34:31,503 --> 00:34:33,004
I WISH I
COULD HELP YOU.

659
00:34:33,004 --> 00:34:35,273
BUT I CAN'T.

660
00:34:35,273 --> 00:34:38,543
CAN I GO BACK
TO CLASS NOW?

661
00:34:43,515 --> 00:34:46,117
PICK YOU UP AFTER
PRACTICE JORDY.

662
00:34:46,685 --> 00:34:48,687
[click]

663
00:34:50,522 --> 00:34:53,425
[door creaks]

664
00:34:58,730 --> 00:35:01,366
WE'RE DEPENDING
   ON YOU REMBRANDT.

665
00:35:01,366 --> 00:35:04,569
I GOT A SCHOLARSHIP
 ON THE LINE.

666
00:35:04,569 --> 00:35:07,105
THEY'RE JUST TRYING
TO SCARE SOMEBODY

667
00:35:07,105 --> 00:35:08,840
INTO POINTING
A FINGER.

668
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:10,875
MAYBE THEY
  SCARED YOU?

669
00:35:10,875 --> 00:35:13,044
NO.

670
00:35:16,014 --> 00:35:18,049
WHAT DOES
 CROWDER KNOW?

671
00:35:18,049 --> 00:35:20,218
HE KNOWS I MISSED
HIS PARTY LAST NIGHT.

672
00:35:20,218 --> 00:35:22,754
HE'S GIVING ME A
RIDE HOME AFTER PRACTICE...

673
00:35:22,754 --> 00:35:25,423
NOT A GOOD IDEA.

674
00:35:25,423 --> 00:35:28,126
WALLY'S A FRIEND.
HE'S MY RIDE.

675
00:35:28,126 --> 00:35:29,995
THAT FOOTBALL SCHOLARSHIP
  IS MY RIDE.

676
00:35:29,995 --> 00:35:31,262
I'M NOT GOING
  TO LET SOME

677
00:35:31,262 --> 00:35:33,198
RELIGIOUS FANATIC
 MESS THAT UP.

678
00:35:33,198 --> 00:35:35,033
LIGHT?
 THANKS.

679
00:35:35,033 --> 00:35:37,402
HEY, YEAH...

680
00:35:40,105 --> 00:35:42,340
NO OFFENSE JORDY -

681
00:35:42,340 --> 00:35:45,643
BUT WE'RE
ALL CHRISTIANS -

682
00:35:45,643 --> 00:35:48,780
BUT WE'RE COOL.

683
00:35:48,780 --> 00:35:51,349
WE DON'T LET IT
GET IN THE WAY.

684
00:35:57,255 --> 00:35:58,790
(sighs)

685
00:35:59,824 --> 00:36:01,726
ALRIGHT, HERE'S
  WHAT WE DO.

686
00:36:01,726 --> 00:36:03,094
WE ORGANIZE
 A JOINT TRIP,

687
00:36:03,094 --> 00:36:04,663
ADVERTISE IN
 BOTH SCHOOLS.

688
00:36:04,663 --> 00:36:06,364
IT'S CLOSE,
 IT'S A NEUTRAL ARENA,

689
00:36:06,364 --> 00:36:08,333
AND IT'S WITHIN
  OUR BUDGET.

690
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:09,801
WALLY, IT'S FREE!

691
00:36:09,801 --> 00:36:11,169
EXACTLY.

692
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:12,203
A COUPLE OF GUYS

693
00:36:12,203 --> 00:36:13,705
FROM WESTBURY PARK
GO TO MY CHURCH.

694
00:36:13,705 --> 00:36:15,507
I CAN GET
THEIR NAMES.

695
00:36:15,507 --> 00:36:16,775
WE'VE GOT FLYERS.

696
00:36:16,775 --> 00:36:18,043
THIS IS A
  PERFECT OPPORTUNITY

697
00:36:18,043 --> 00:36:19,477
TO BE PEACEMAKERS.

698
00:36:19,477 --> 00:36:20,812
WELL THEN, LET'S
 GET STARTED.

699
00:36:20,812 --> 00:36:23,214
ALRIGHT,
  LET'S PRAY.

700
00:36:23,214 --> 00:36:26,351
DEAR LORD, WE ASK
   FOR YOUR STRENGTH

701
00:36:26,351 --> 00:36:28,053
AND YOUR GUIDANCE
   IN THE COMING DAYS

702
00:36:28,053 --> 00:36:30,522
AS WE SEEK PEACE
  IN THIS CONFLICT...

703
00:36:45,503 --> 00:36:49,908
[bell chimes]

704
00:36:49,908 --> 00:36:52,077
THIS IS A GREAT CAUSE.

705
00:36:52,077 --> 00:36:53,545
IF I COULD JUST LEAVE A
  FEW...

706
00:36:53,545 --> 00:36:55,213
IT'S AGAINST SCHOOL POLICY.

707
00:36:55,213 --> 00:36:56,481
WHO'S YOUR BOSS?

708
00:36:56,481 --> 00:36:57,682
FRITZ GOLDMAN.

709
00:36:57,682 --> 00:36:58,716
IS HE AVAILABLE?

710
00:36:58,716 --> 00:36:59,784
HE'S IN A MEETING.

711
00:36:59,784 --> 00:37:00,952
AVAILABLE AT LUNCH?

712
00:37:00,952 --> 00:37:01,786
NO, HE'S BUSY.

713
00:37:01,786 --> 00:37:02,754
I'LL BE BACK AFTER SCHOOL.

714
00:37:02,754 --> 00:37:04,322
DEAN GOLDMAN
IS NOT AVAILABLE.

715
00:37:04,322 --> 00:37:05,657
PLEASE, IT'S A REALLY GOOD
  CAUSE.

716
00:37:05,657 --> 00:37:07,759
DO WHAT YOU
HAVE TO DO.

717
00:37:10,061 --> 00:37:14,265
[bell rings]

718
00:37:14,265 --> 00:37:20,138
[engine roars]

719
00:37:20,138 --> 00:37:25,510
[bell ringing]

720
00:37:25,510 --> 00:37:30,682
[engines roaring]

721
00:37:35,253 --> 00:37:40,759
[ominous vocal chorus]

722
00:37:40,759 --> 00:37:44,429
PASS ME.
PASS ME ALREADY!

723
00:37:45,730 --> 00:37:48,867
[screech... clunk]

724
00:37:51,836 --> 00:37:54,405
OWN THE ROAD BUDDY! GO FOR IT!

725
00:37:55,974 --> 00:37:59,410
[roar... screech]

726
00:37:59,410 --> 00:38:04,883
♪ [ominous] ♪

727
00:38:07,552 --> 00:38:09,654
[starter motor whirs]

728
00:38:18,196 --> 00:38:22,500
[smash... crash!]

729
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:30,742
[motor roars]

730
00:38:30,742 --> 00:38:33,611
[screeching]

731
00:38:33,611 --> 00:38:41,052
♪ [ominous] ♪

732
00:38:41,052 --> 00:38:44,522
[blam, screech, smash]

733
00:38:44,522 --> 00:38:54,332
♪    ♪♪

734
00:38:54,332 --> 00:38:56,935
THIS IS DEAN STAVERMAN.

735
00:38:56,935 --> 00:39:00,338
I HAVE AN IMPORTANT
ANNOUNCEMENT TO MAKE.

736
00:39:00,338 --> 00:39:04,142
GOOD MORNING,
THIS IS DEAN GOLDMAN.

737
00:39:04,142 --> 00:39:07,645
(Dean Staverman) 
YESTERDAY AT APPROXIMATELY 6:00
PM,

738
00:39:07,645 --> 00:39:10,481
MORRIS STUDENT BODY PRESIDENT,
WALLY CROWDER,

739
00:39:10,481 --> 00:39:15,053
WAS INVOLVED IN A TERRIBLE CAR
ACCIDENT ON SEAVEY ROAD.

740
00:39:15,053 --> 00:39:19,190
(Dean Goldman) 
WE DON'T HAVE ANY INFORMATION AT
THIS TIME,

741
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:22,227
HOWEVER, THE POLICE HAVE
CONFIRMED...

742
00:39:22,227 --> 00:39:23,728
(Staverman) 
...THAT HE WAS TAKEN BY
AMBULANCE

743
00:39:23,728 --> 00:39:25,697
TO ST. FRANCIS HOSPITAL.

744
00:39:25,697 --> 00:39:29,067
HE WAS TRAVELING ALONE
AT THE TIME...

745
00:39:29,067 --> 00:39:31,736
(Goldman) 
IT APPEARS THAT NO OTHER
VEHICLES WERE INVOLVED,

746
00:39:31,736 --> 00:39:33,972
AND NO ONE ELSE WAS INJURED.

747
00:39:33,972 --> 00:39:35,540
(Staverman) 
OUR THOUGHTS AND PRAYERS

748
00:39:35,540 --> 00:39:37,508
GO OUT TO HIM AND HIS FAMILY.

749
00:39:37,508 --> 00:39:39,010
(Goldman) 
A TRAGEDY LIKE THIS

750
00:39:39,010 --> 00:39:41,412
AFFECTS THE ENTIRE SCHOOL.

751
00:39:41,412 --> 00:39:43,948
(Staverman) 
THIS IS A VERY SAD DAY FOR ALL
OF US.

752
00:39:43,948 --> 00:39:47,819
THE BEST THING WE CAN DO IS TO
HOLD OUT GOOD THOUGHTS

753
00:39:47,819 --> 00:39:50,822
FOR OUR FRIEND, WALLY CROWDER.

754
00:39:50,822 --> 00:39:53,825
WE HOPE TO GET WORD FROM THE
HOSPITAL SHORTLY

755
00:39:53,825 --> 00:39:56,060
ON HOW HE'S DOING.

756
00:39:56,060 --> 00:39:59,063
THAT'S ALL FOR NOW.

757
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:05,236
♪ [melodic orchestral] ♪

758
00:40:11,175 --> 00:40:14,479
MRS. CROWDER, YOU CAN
 COME IN NOW.

759
00:40:14,479 --> 00:40:16,514
(Pam)
HE'S GOING TO BE OKAY THEN?

760
00:40:16,514 --> 00:40:18,883
(Dr. Allen)
WE'RE JUST KEEPING A CLOSE EYE
ON HIM RIGHT NOW.

761
00:40:18,883 --> 00:40:20,351
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

762
00:40:20,351 --> 00:40:21,853
HE'S A GOOD PERSON MY
   BOY,

763
00:40:21,853 --> 00:40:24,489
WHY WOULD ANYBODY
   WANT TO HURT MY BABY.

764
00:40:33,298 --> 00:40:36,601
(Jake)
WE CAME BY TO EXTEND OUR
APOLOGIES.

765
00:40:38,670 --> 00:40:40,071
WHO'S RESPONSIBLE?

766
00:40:40,071 --> 00:40:40,972
WE DON'T KNOW.

767
00:40:40,972 --> 00:40:42,106
NONE OF US.

768
00:40:42,106 --> 00:40:44,108
ALL OF US.

769
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:46,210
WE WANT TO PUT AN END
 TO THIS THING LIKE HE
 DID.

770
00:40:46,210 --> 00:40:49,347
IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND
 GIVING HIM THE MESSAGE.

771
00:40:49,347 --> 00:40:52,183
WE PLAN ON BEING THERE.

772
00:40:52,183 --> 00:40:53,985
(Pam)
WALLY TRIED TO DROP OFF SOME
FLYERS...

773
00:40:53,985 --> 00:40:56,621
(Jake)
WE'LL BE THERE AND WE'LL BE
PRAYING.

774
00:40:56,621 --> 00:40:59,524
THAT'S GREAT!

775
00:40:59,524 --> 00:41:01,392
HE'LL REALLY
APPRECIATE THAT!

776
00:41:01,392 --> 00:41:03,628
NOW I'VE GOT A MESSAGE FOR THE
GUYS THAT DID THIS.

777
00:41:03,628 --> 00:41:05,129
WE'D LIKE TO SETTLE THIS ONCE
AND FOR ALL.

778
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:06,698
ANYBODY THAT'S GOT THE GUTS.

779
00:41:06,698 --> 00:41:09,033
JORDY! THIS HAS
   GONE TOO FAR.
3:00. MONDAY.

780
00:41:09,033 --> 00:41:10,735
SAME FIELD
WHERE IT HAPPENED.

781
00:41:10,735 --> 00:41:12,704
ANYBODY THAT'S
GOT THE GUTS.

782
00:41:12,704 --> 00:41:16,374
YOU TELL THEM
I'LL BE THERE.

783
00:41:25,616 --> 00:41:27,085
[BANG!]

784
00:41:33,057 --> 00:41:35,059
(reading) 
"DEAR JORDY,

785
00:41:35,059 --> 00:41:38,262
DON'T BECOME SO WELL ADJUSTED
TO YOUR CULTURE

786
00:41:38,262 --> 00:41:41,099
THAT YOU FIT INTO IT
WITHOUT EVEN THINKING.

787
00:41:41,099 --> 00:41:43,801
FIX YOUR ATTENTION ON GOD.

788
00:41:43,801 --> 00:41:46,504
YOU'LL BE CHANGED
FROM THE INSIDE OUT.

789
00:41:46,504 --> 00:41:49,707
WE GOT TO FIGHT TO DO
WHAT'S RIGHT BROTHER,

790
00:41:49,707 --> 00:41:52,410
WALLY."

791
00:41:59,016 --> 00:42:03,187
(Dr. Billy Graham) 
THERE'S SO MUCH
DISEASE AND POVERTY

792
00:42:03,187 --> 00:42:06,657
AND WAR AND HATE
AND LONELINESS,

793
00:42:06,657 --> 00:42:12,096
UNEMPLOYMENT, BOREDOM,
SOCIAL INJUSTICE,

794
00:42:12,096 --> 00:42:17,034
RACIAL PROBLEMS,
PSYCHOLOGICAL PROBLEMS, AIDS.

795
00:42:17,034 --> 00:42:20,004
ALL OF THESE THINGS
ARE PUSHING IN ON US.

796
00:42:20,004 --> 00:42:22,774
AT A TIME, IT SEEMS TO ME,
WHEN WE OUGHT TO HAVE

797
00:42:22,774 --> 00:42:26,844
A MARVELOUS WORLD
OF PEACE AND LOVE.

798
00:42:26,844 --> 00:42:29,747
WHAT'S WRONG?

799
00:42:29,747 --> 00:42:33,051
AND YOUNG PEOPLE ARE ASKING
THAT QUESTION:  WHY?

800
00:42:33,051 --> 00:42:37,355
WHAT'S GOING TO BECOME OF US?
WHAT'S WRONG WITH THE WORLD?

801
00:42:37,355 --> 00:42:40,691
IS THERE AN ANSWER TO IT ALL?

802
00:42:40,691 --> 00:42:43,060
DOES ANYBODY CARE?

803
00:42:43,060 --> 00:42:46,597
DOES ANYBODY REALLY LOVE YOU?

804
00:42:46,597 --> 00:42:50,635
YOU ARE ABSOLUTELY
IMPORTANT TO GOD.

805
00:42:50,635 --> 00:42:55,206
JUST AS THOUGH YOU WERE THE ONLY
PERSON THAT EVER LIVED.

806
00:42:55,206 --> 00:42:58,109
AND GOD LOVES YOU.

807
00:42:58,109 --> 00:43:02,013
AND HE WANTS TO FORGIVE YOU OF
YOUR FAILURES AND YOUR SINS,

808
00:43:02,013 --> 00:43:05,850
ALL THE WAY BACK TO THE TIME
THAT YOU CAN REMEMBER.

809
00:43:05,850 --> 00:43:09,220
HE'S WILLING TO
FORGIVE YOU TONIGHT.

810
00:43:09,220 --> 00:43:13,091
AND COVER IT UP AS THOUGH
IT HAD NEVER HAPPENED.

811
00:43:13,091 --> 00:43:16,894
GOD DOESN'T JUST SAY, "I LOVE
YA, I FORGIVE YA."

812
00:43:16,894 --> 00:43:19,063
HE DOES SOMETHING ABOUT IT.

813
00:43:19,063 --> 00:43:22,300
HE SENT HIS SON, CHRIST,
TO DIE ON THE CROSS.

814
00:43:22,300 --> 00:43:23,935
AND WHEN CHRIST DIED
ON THAT CROSS,

815
00:43:23,935 --> 00:43:28,139
HE TOOK YOUR SINS AND MY SINS
ON HIMSELF.

816
00:43:28,139 --> 00:43:31,409
AND HE TOOK MY SINS
AND YOUR SINS

817
00:43:31,409 --> 00:43:34,779
AND BURIED THEM
IN THE DEPTHS OF THE SEA.

818
00:43:34,779 --> 00:43:37,715
AND HE FORGETS THEM.

819
00:43:37,715 --> 00:43:41,219
WELL, YOU SAY, "BILLY, I KNOW
THAT JESUS DID ALL THAT FOR US

820
00:43:41,219 --> 00:43:43,988
BECAUSE HE LOVED US.
I KNOW THAT.

821
00:43:43,988 --> 00:43:46,157
BUT WHAT DO WE HAVE TO DO?"

822
00:43:46,157 --> 00:43:49,527
FIRST - YOU HAVE TO
REPENT OF YOUR SINS.

823
00:43:49,527 --> 00:43:52,063
JESUS SAID, "I CAME NOT
TO CALL THE RIGHTEOUS,

824
00:43:52,063 --> 00:43:54,398
BUT SINNERS, TO REPENTANCE."

825
00:43:54,398 --> 00:43:56,167
SOME LITTLE BOY SAID,

826
00:43:56,167 --> 00:43:58,803
"REPENTANCE MEANS BEING
SORRY ENOUGH TO QUIT."

827
00:43:58,803 --> 00:44:01,172
THAT'S A PRETTY GOOD DEFINITION.

828
00:44:01,172 --> 00:44:04,876
AND THEN THE SECOND THING
IS FAITH.

829
00:44:04,876 --> 00:44:08,012
WITHOUT FAITH, IT IS IMPOSSIBLE
TO PLEASE GOD.

830
00:44:08,012 --> 00:44:10,181
YOU SAY, "WELL, WHAT DOES
THAT MEAN?"

831
00:44:10,181 --> 00:44:12,717
IT'S NOT SOMETHING YOU WORK UP.

832
00:44:12,717 --> 00:44:14,719
IT'S NOT SOMETHING YOU DO WITH
YOUR HEAD.

833
00:44:14,719 --> 00:44:16,754
IT'S SOMETHING THAT YOU DO WITH
YOUR BODY.

834
00:44:16,754 --> 00:44:18,156
WITH YOUR HEART.

835
00:44:18,156 --> 00:44:19,991
WITH YOUR EMOTIONS.

836
00:44:19,991 --> 00:44:21,692
WITH EVERYTHING YOU HAVE, YOU
SAY,

837
00:44:21,692 --> 00:44:24,395
"I GIVE MYSELF TO CHRIST."

838
00:44:24,395 --> 00:44:29,400
THE THIRD THING--
YOU MUST OBEY HIM.

839
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:31,435
YOU MUST LIVE FOR HIM.

840
00:44:31,435 --> 00:44:33,804
AND I'M GOING TO ASK YOU TONIGHT

841
00:44:33,804 --> 00:44:35,840
TO RECEIVE CHRIST
INTO YOUR HEART.

842
00:44:35,840 --> 00:44:40,545
AND LIVE FOR HIM THE BEST YOU
CAN WITH HIS HELP.

843
00:44:40,545 --> 00:44:43,314
I'M GOING TO ASK YOU
TO STAND TO YOUR FEET.

844
00:44:43,314 --> 00:44:46,250
I'M NOT ASKING YOU TO
JOIN ANY ORGANIZATION

845
00:44:46,250 --> 00:44:47,818
OR ANYTHING LIKE THAT,

846
00:44:47,818 --> 00:44:52,056
I'M JUST ASKING YOU TO RECEIVE
CHRIST INTO YOUR HEART.

847
00:44:52,056 --> 00:44:53,791
TONIGHT IS A GOOD STARTING PLACE

848
00:44:53,791 --> 00:44:55,293
WITH ALL THESE PEOPLE HERE

849
00:44:55,293 --> 00:44:57,161
AND MANY THOUSANDS
OF PEOPLE PRAYING.

850
00:44:57,161 --> 00:44:59,630
YOU CAN GET STARTED AND SAY,

851
00:44:59,630 --> 00:45:03,067
"LORD, I WANT TO START,

852
00:45:03,067 --> 00:45:05,670
MAYBE AFRESH OR ANEW WITH YOU.

853
00:45:05,670 --> 00:45:07,838
I'VE BEEN SORT OF A FAILURE
UP 'TIL NOW.

854
00:45:07,838 --> 00:45:09,974
I BELIEVE,
BUT I HAVEN'T BELIEVED.

855
00:45:09,974 --> 00:45:13,978
THAT'S WHAT YOU NEED TO DO
TONIGHT, IS TO GET STARTED."

856
00:45:13,978 --> 00:45:17,415
YOU SAY, "BUT I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO PRAY."

857
00:45:17,415 --> 00:45:20,718
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
PRAY LIKE A PREACHER.

858
00:45:20,718 --> 00:45:23,554
YOU JUST TALK TO GOD

859
00:45:23,554 --> 00:45:26,791
AS THOUGH HE WERE YOUR BEST
FRIEND WHICH HE IS.

860
00:45:26,791 --> 00:45:28,426
TELL HIM EVERYTHING.

861
00:45:28,426 --> 00:45:29,794
SAY, "LORD I LOVE YOU.

862
00:45:29,794 --> 00:45:32,396
I... I PRAISE YOU.

863
00:45:32,396 --> 00:45:35,232
I THANK YOU."

864
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:38,135
AND THEN SAY, "LORD,
I NEED SOME HELP.

865
00:45:38,135 --> 00:45:40,237
PLEASE HELP ME."

866
00:45:40,237 --> 00:45:43,474
PRAY IT IN THE NAME OF JESUS.

867
00:45:43,474 --> 00:45:46,544
AND HE'LL HELP YOU.

868
00:45:46,544 --> 00:45:48,946
HE ANSWERS EVERY PRAYER.

869
00:45:52,516 --> 00:45:54,552
YOU GET THE GAS,

870
00:45:54,552 --> 00:45:55,953
THROW IT UP ON THERE...

871
00:45:55,953 --> 00:45:57,989
VAROOM!!

872
00:46:03,127 --> 00:46:05,896
MAY I HAVE
YOUR ATTENTION PLEASE?

873
00:46:05,896 --> 00:46:08,232
WE'RE GOING TO
KEEP THIS REAL SHORT.

874
00:46:08,232 --> 00:46:10,468
AFTER DISCUSSIONS
WITH THE ADMINISTRATION

875
00:46:10,468 --> 00:46:12,703
AT WESTBURY PARK HIGH SCHOOL,

876
00:46:12,703 --> 00:46:16,007
WE HAVE DECIDED TO CANCEL
THIS YEAR'S HOMECOMING.

877
00:46:16,007 --> 00:46:17,441
[many students]
WHY? WHAT FOR?

878
00:46:17,441 --> 00:46:19,610
QUIET! QUIET!

879
00:46:19,610 --> 00:46:22,980
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S ENOUGH!
SIT DOWN!

880
00:46:22,980 --> 00:46:26,317
I'VE ASKED PAM FOSTER
TO SPEAK TO YOU

881
00:46:26,317 --> 00:46:29,620
ON BEHALF OF
THE STUDENT GOVERNMENT-- PAM.

882
00:46:33,124 --> 00:46:37,061
WALLY CROWDER ASKED ME
TO READ THE FOLLOWING LETTER:

883
00:46:37,061 --> 00:46:39,864
"MY FELLOW GRIZZLIES.

884
00:46:39,864 --> 00:46:44,101
I KNOW THINGS ARE STILL TENSE.

885
00:46:44,101 --> 00:46:46,504
EVERYBODY'S GOTTA
FOLLOW SOMEBODY.

886
00:46:46,504 --> 00:46:49,707
I REALIZE IT ISN'T
GOING TO BE ME.

887
00:46:49,707 --> 00:46:54,612
THEREFORE, I OFFER MY
RESIGNATION AS YOUR PRESIDENT.

888
00:46:54,612 --> 00:46:57,982
[clears her throat]

889
00:46:57,982 --> 00:47:00,051
SECONDLY, I WANT YOU TO KNOW

890
00:47:00,051 --> 00:47:02,319
THAT I FORGIVE THE GUYS
THAT DID THIS.

891
00:47:02,319 --> 00:47:04,855
AND I HOPE YOU WILL TOO.

892
00:47:04,855 --> 00:47:06,957
THE CHOICE IS REALLY YOURS.

893
00:47:06,957 --> 00:47:09,427
CONTINUE THIS CHILDISH FEUD

894
00:47:09,427 --> 00:47:11,595
OR RESOLVE OUR DIFFERENCES

895
00:47:11,595 --> 00:47:14,965
LIKE RESPONSIBLE CITIZENS
AND CHRISTIANS.

896
00:47:14,965 --> 00:47:17,868
THE FUTURE IS IN OUR HANDS.

897
00:47:17,868 --> 00:47:21,972
PEACE, WALLY."

898
00:47:21,972 --> 00:47:24,308
SO WHAT ARE WE
GONNA DO, GUYS?

899
00:47:24,308 --> 00:47:27,344
CONTINUE THIS CHILDISH FEUD

900
00:47:27,344 --> 00:47:31,048
OR RESOLVE OUR DIFFERENCES?

901
00:47:35,653 --> 00:47:37,388
CHILDISH FEUD!

902
00:47:37,388 --> 00:47:40,458
(other students)
 CHILDISH FEUD! CHILDISH FEUD!
 CHILDISH FEUD!

903
00:47:40,458 --> 00:47:43,227
(more join in)
 CHILDISH FEUD!
FEUD! FEUD! FEUD! FEUD!

904
00:47:43,227 --> 00:47:46,897
FEUD! FEUD! FEUD! FEUD!

905
00:47:49,467 --> 00:47:52,903
JORDY! JORDY!
 JORDY! JORDY!!

906
00:47:52,903 --> 00:47:55,973
JOR-DY! JOR-DY!
JOR-DY! JOR-DY!!

907
00:47:55,973 --> 00:48:03,314
JOR-DY!
   JOR-DY! JOR-DY! JOR-DY!!

908
00:48:05,816 --> 00:48:08,085
CAN I SAY SOMETHING, PLEASE?

909
00:48:08,085 --> 00:48:11,822
MOST OF YOU ALREADY KNOW THIS.

910
00:48:11,822 --> 00:48:16,160
I WAS INVOLVED IN
THE INCIDENT AT WESTBURY PARK.

911
00:48:16,160 --> 00:48:18,996
I'M, AH...

912
00:48:18,996 --> 00:48:22,166
I'M RESPONSIBLE
FOR WHAT HAPPENED.

913
00:48:22,166 --> 00:48:24,468
ALRIGHT... YEAH
[much cheering]

914
00:48:24,468 --> 00:48:26,871
(speaking forcefully)
AND WHAT I DID WAS...

915
00:48:26,871 --> 00:48:29,707
WHAT I DID WAS WRONG.

916
00:48:29,707 --> 00:48:33,978
A FRIEND OF MINE WAS ALMOST
KILLED BECAUSE OF ME.

917
00:48:33,978 --> 00:48:38,616
I HAVE SOME UNFINISHED BUSINESS
WITH OUR CROSS-TOWN RIVALS.

918
00:48:38,616 --> 00:48:42,820
ANYBODY THAT'S GOT THE GUTS...

919
00:48:42,820 --> 00:48:47,191
FOLLOW ME.

920
00:48:49,994 --> 00:48:54,031
REMBRANDT!!

921
00:48:56,801 --> 00:49:07,344
♪ [strings-- suspenseful] ♪

922
00:49:07,344 --> 00:49:09,713
HE'S GONNA GET
   KILLED.

923
00:49:09,713 --> 00:49:12,716
YEAH... LET'S GO WATCH.

924
00:49:12,716 --> 00:49:18,556
♪    ♪

925
00:49:18,556 --> 00:49:22,526
[angry yelling]

926
00:49:22,526 --> 00:49:24,528
AGAIN, I'M SORRY.
HOMECOMING'S BEEN CANCELED.

927
00:49:24,528 --> 00:49:26,497
THIS MATTER'S GOTTEN
WAY OUT OF CONTROL.

928
00:49:26,497 --> 00:49:28,299
PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE...

929
00:49:28,299 --> 00:49:32,169
QUIET, PLEASE!
QUIET, PLEASE!!

930
00:49:32,169 --> 00:49:33,737
GRIZZLIES ON THE MOVE!

931
00:49:33,737 --> 00:49:35,473
THE WHOLE SCHOOL
   IS MARCHING ON US.

932
00:49:35,473 --> 00:49:36,941
THEY'RE IN
FISHER'S FIELD!

933
00:49:36,941 --> 00:49:38,375
LET'S GO,
   COME ON!

934
00:49:38,375 --> 00:49:40,978
YOU ARE NOT DISMISSED!
YOU ARE NOT DISMISSED!

935
00:49:40,978 --> 00:49:43,480
[much yelling]
STAY IN YOUR SEATS
UNTIL YOU'RE DISMISSED!

936
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:46,050
[bell rings]
OKAY. YOU CAN GO.

937
00:49:46,050 --> 00:49:57,895
♪ [throbbing bass, strings] ♪

938
00:49:57,895 --> 00:50:05,135
♪ [throbbing bass, strings &
   powerful vocal chorus] ♪

