00:51:17,841 --> 00:51:19,109
(Jordy)
YOU'RE GOING TO DESTROY US?

951
00:51:19,109 --> 00:51:20,244
YOU'RE A DEAD MAN,
   REMBRANDT!

952
00:51:20,244 --> 00:51:21,345
YEAH, I AM.

953
00:51:21,345 --> 00:51:22,713
AS OF THIS WEEKEND ACTUALLY.

954
00:51:22,713 --> 00:51:24,148
IT'S PAY BACK TIME.

955
00:51:24,148 --> 00:51:26,750
AND I INTEND TO. EVERY CENT.

956
00:51:26,750 --> 00:51:28,252
YOU TORCHED
OUR BUS!

957
00:51:28,252 --> 00:51:29,753
YEAH, I DID.

958
00:51:29,753 --> 00:51:31,822
YOU'RE ADMITTING IT?

959
00:51:31,822 --> 00:51:34,024
YEAH. AND I APOLOGIZE.

960
00:51:34,024 --> 00:51:36,226
I'LL DO WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO MAKE IT RIGHT.

961
00:51:36,226 --> 00:51:38,329
WE DIDN'T TOAST
YOUR FLOAT MAN.

962
00:51:38,329 --> 00:51:40,564
YEAH, I GOT AN IDEA
  ON THAT TOO.

963
00:51:40,564 --> 00:51:43,200
THE KID IN THE CAR
ALL RIGHT?

964
00:51:43,200 --> 00:51:46,337
YEAH. HE'S GOING
  TO BE ALL RIGHT.

965
00:51:50,507 --> 00:52:07,191
♪  ♪

966
00:52:07,191 --> 00:52:09,360
SEE YOU ON
ANOTHER FIELD SOMETIME?

967
00:52:09,360 --> 00:52:11,428
DEAL.

968
00:52:11,428 --> 00:52:15,399
♪ [piano & strings] ♪

969
00:52:15,399 --> 00:52:34,985
♪  ♪

970
00:52:38,722 --> 00:52:41,091
[car door slams]

971
00:52:43,627 --> 00:52:46,030
[knocking on door]

972
00:52:50,567 --> 00:52:51,769
HEY.

973
00:53:10,454 --> 00:53:12,256
[gasps]...

974
00:53:13,891 --> 00:53:16,160
I HAD NO IDEA.
I JUST THOUGHT...

975
00:53:16,160 --> 00:53:18,629
(Wally)
IT DOESN'T MAKE ANY DIFFERENCE.

976
00:53:23,133 --> 00:53:25,936
HOW'D IT HAPPEN?

977
00:53:25,936 --> 00:53:27,871
MESSING AROUND.

978
00:53:27,871 --> 00:53:30,340
IN A POOL.

979
00:53:30,340 --> 00:53:33,043
I WAS A SWIMMER.

980
00:53:33,043 --> 00:53:35,145
WHEN?

981
00:53:35,145 --> 00:53:37,347
4 YEARS AGO.

982
00:53:39,550 --> 00:53:42,553
YOU NEVER THINK IT CAN
   HAPPEN TO YOU.

983
00:53:42,553 --> 00:53:46,390
ANYWAY. WHAT'S UP?

984
00:53:46,390 --> 00:53:48,826
SO... THE GAME'S ON TOMORROW.

985
00:53:48,826 --> 00:53:50,761
I HEARD THAT.
   THAT'S GREAT.

986
00:53:50,761 --> 00:53:53,430
I JUST THOUGHT IF YOU FELT UP TO
IT YOU COULD COME BY...

987
00:53:53,430 --> 00:53:56,967
I DON'T. BUT THANKS.

988
00:53:59,203 --> 00:54:02,739
WELL THEN, I JUST CAME BY
TO SAY THANKS.

989
00:54:05,442 --> 00:54:09,980
YOU CAME BY BECAUSE YOU
   FELT SORRY FOR ME--
   DON'T.

990
00:54:09,980 --> 00:54:14,017
I CAME BY TO TELL YOU
YOU WERE RIGHT.

991
00:54:16,787 --> 00:54:19,189
IT'S BEEN A REAL FIGHT BUT AH...

992
00:54:19,189 --> 00:54:21,225
I THINK I'M DOING
THE RIGHT THING.

993
00:54:21,225 --> 00:54:24,361
FOR ONCE IN MY LIFE.

994
00:54:32,369 --> 00:54:35,572
I WENT AND HEARD
BILLY GRAHAM.

995
00:54:39,309 --> 00:54:40,811
HE SAID IT TOO.

996
00:54:40,811 --> 00:54:43,280
"EVERYBODY'S GOT TO FOLLOW
SOMEBODY," RIGHT?

997
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:47,151
I CAME BY TO SAY THANKS
FOR BEING AN EXAMPLE

998
00:54:47,151 --> 00:54:50,888
OF WHAT IT IS TO FOLLOW JESUS.

999
00:54:53,090 --> 00:54:57,861
I HOPE THAT SOMEDAY YOU CAN
ACCEPT MY APOLOGY...

1000
00:54:57,861 --> 00:55:00,330
FOR EVERYTHING.

1001
00:55:02,533 --> 00:55:05,002
I'M DEDICATING THE GAME
TOMORROW, TO YOU.

1002
00:55:05,002 --> 00:55:08,172
DID YOU REALLY JORDY?

1003
00:55:08,172 --> 00:55:11,909
DID YOU INVITE CHRIST
   INTO YOUR HEART?

1004
00:55:11,909 --> 00:55:16,513
YEAH. I DID.

1005
00:55:16,513 --> 00:55:19,950
THEN DEDICATE
   IT TO HIM.

1006
00:55:19,950 --> 00:55:22,819
AND YOU RUN
   THOSE BADGERS BACK

1007
00:55:22,819 --> 00:55:25,722
INTO THE DARK HOLE WHERE
   THEY BELONG.

1008
00:55:25,722 --> 00:55:26,990
(chuckles)

1009
00:55:26,990 --> 00:55:29,526
[grunting]

1010
00:55:29,526 --> 00:55:31,595
[cheering]

1011
00:55:31,595 --> 00:55:34,398
(announcer) 
PASS TO #20-- JORDY REMBRANDT!

1012
00:55:38,468 --> 00:55:41,705
NICE CATCH!
NICE HIT!

1013
00:55:44,041 --> 00:55:46,944
(announcer) 
THAT'S THE BALLGAME!

1014
00:55:46,944 --> 00:55:49,880
THANK YOU
GOOD GAME!

1015
00:55:49,880 --> 00:55:52,316
PICK UP YOUR TICKETS FOR
HOMECOMING

1016
00:55:52,316 --> 00:55:54,117
AND HAVE A GREAT WEEK.

1017
00:55:54,117 --> 00:55:57,020
LET'S GIVE A NICE ROUND OF
APPLAUSE FOR THE KIWANIS CLUB

1018
00:55:57,020 --> 00:55:59,356
FOR SUPPLYING ALL THE GREAT
UNSALTED PEANUTS.

1019
00:55:59,356 --> 00:56:01,792
SEE YA NEXT WEEK!

1020
00:56:01,792 --> 00:56:03,727
(Jordy)
ANY SIGN OF HIM?

1021
00:56:03,727 --> 00:56:06,430
(Pam)
NO... WE TRIED BUT...

1022
00:56:06,430 --> 00:56:08,999
HE'S STILL
  PRETTY BANGED UP...

1023
00:56:08,999 --> 00:56:11,201
INSIDE.

1024
00:56:11,201 --> 00:56:14,638
(Jordy)
I GUESS I OWE YOU AN APOLOGY
TOO.

1025
00:56:14,638 --> 00:56:18,508
IT'S NOT ENTIRELY
   YOUR FAULT.

1026
00:56:18,508 --> 00:56:20,777
YOU'RE A GUY.
Y'KNOW GUYS ARE DUMB.

1027
00:56:20,777 --> 00:56:22,746
THANKS PAM.

1028
00:56:24,181 --> 00:56:26,483
FOR WHAT?

1029
00:56:26,483 --> 00:56:29,353
KEEPING ME
 CLOSE TO SHORE.

1030
00:56:29,353 --> 00:56:30,921
(Dean Staverman)
AND THE KING AND QUEEN

1031
00:56:30,921 --> 00:56:33,390
OF MORRIS HIGH SCHOOL'S
HOMECOMING IS...

1032
00:56:33,390 --> 00:56:34,891
I AM PROUD TO PRESENT...

1033
00:56:34,891 --> 00:56:38,562
JORDY REMBRANDT
AND MICHELLE STARK!

1034
00:56:38,562 --> 00:56:39,963
[applause]

1035
00:56:39,963 --> 00:56:42,566
I... I GUESS YOU BETTER GO.

1036
00:56:42,566 --> 00:56:44,735
YEAH.

1037
00:56:47,804 --> 00:56:50,807
SMILE, DUDE, THIS
 ISN'T A FUNERAL.

1038
00:56:50,807 --> 00:56:53,343
(Wags)
HEY MAN, LOOK WHO YOU'RE
STANDING NEXT TO.

1039
00:56:53,343 --> 00:56:57,180
[applause]

1040
00:56:59,249 --> 00:57:03,687
♪ [strings, oboe] ♪

1041
00:57:03,687 --> 00:57:05,422
[click]

1042
00:57:05,422 --> 00:57:07,157
[click]

1043
00:57:07,157 --> 00:57:08,425
[click]

1044
00:57:08,425 --> 00:57:09,393
[click]

1045
00:57:09,393 --> 00:57:10,494
[click]

1046
00:57:10,494 --> 00:57:11,395
[click]

1047
00:57:11,395 --> 00:58:08,585
♪    ♪

1048
00:58:10,787 --> 00:58:11,988
NICE SUIT!

1049
00:58:11,988 --> 00:58:13,757
THANKS. STRAIGHT
OFF THE RACK.

1050
00:58:13,757 --> 00:58:15,425
YA! SHOULD'VE
 STAYED THERE.

1051
00:58:18,061 --> 00:58:21,298
WELL, HERE'S SOMETHING

1052
00:58:21,298 --> 00:58:23,700
I NEVER THOUGHT
   I'D BE ABLE TO RETURN--

1053
00:58:23,700 --> 00:58:26,970
YOUR FRIENDSHIP.

1054
00:58:30,407 --> 00:58:33,110
YOU'VE TAUGHT ME A LOT
   WALLY.

1055
00:58:36,480 --> 00:58:38,648
NOBODY DESERVES THIS MORE
   THAN YOU.

1056
00:58:41,184 --> 00:58:43,353
WELL, WHAT DO YOU SAY, WALLY?

1057
00:58:43,353 --> 00:58:46,590
THANKS, JORDY.

1058
00:58:48,291 --> 00:58:50,427
I'M GENUINELY TOUCHED.

1059
00:58:55,165 --> 00:58:59,736
HEY-- I WONDER HOW MUCH THIS
THING IS WORTH MELTED DOWN?

1060
00:59:02,739 --> 00:59:05,675
SO, MAY I HAVE THE HONOR?

1061
00:59:05,675 --> 00:59:08,578
BY ALL MEANS.

1062
00:59:08,578 --> 00:59:14,851
♪ [violins
rising in intensity] ♪

1063
00:59:14,851 --> 00:59:17,487
(Jordy) 
Y'KNOW, GOD MADE EACH OF US
UNIQUE...

1064
00:59:17,487 --> 00:59:19,556
AND WE SPEND OUR WHOLE LIVES

1065
00:59:19,556 --> 00:59:21,825
TRYING TO BE LIKE EVERYONE ELSE.

1066
00:59:21,825 --> 00:59:24,528
THIS WAS MY HOMECOMING.

1067
00:59:24,528 --> 00:59:27,864
FINDING THE LOVE OF GOD AND THE
LOVE OF HIS FOLLOWERS.

1068
00:59:27,864 --> 00:59:32,702
TO BE ACCEPTED...
JUST AS I AM.

1069
00:59:32,702 --> 00:59:35,539
EVERYBODY'S GOT TO FOLLOW
SOMEBODY.

1070
00:59:35,539 --> 00:59:38,842
THE WAY HOME IS SIMPLE.

1071
00:59:38,842 --> 00:59:42,646
JESUS SAID IT BEST...

1072
00:59:42,646 --> 00:59:44,815
"FOLLOW ME."

